WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.465 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.465 --> 00:00:13.880 align:middle line:90%


00:00:13.880 --> 00:00:16.129 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, I'm
Lisa Garr, and welcome.

00:00:16.129 --> 00:00:18.040 align:middle line:84%
Do you think that
the power of prayer

00:00:18.040 --> 00:00:20.270 align:middle line:90%
has an effect on healing?

00:00:20.270 --> 00:00:22.780 align:middle line:84%
My guest today has helped
change the face of medicine

00:00:22.780 --> 00:00:26.690 align:middle line:84%
with his groundbreaking studies
on the scientific connection

00:00:26.690 --> 00:00:29.110 align:middle line:84%
between science
and spirituality.

00:00:29.110 --> 00:00:32.790 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Larry Dossey has provided
the scientific and medical

00:00:32.790 --> 00:00:36.730 align:middle line:84%
proof that spiritual
dimensions work in healing.

00:00:36.730 --> 00:00:40.140 align:middle line:84%
Coming from his background as
an internal medicine doctor,

00:00:40.140 --> 00:00:43.010 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Dossey has been able
to change the curriculum

00:00:43.010 --> 00:00:45.290 align:middle line:90%
in hundreds of medical schools.

00:00:45.290 --> 00:00:47.210 align:middle line:84%
His book, "Healing
Words," is now

00:00:47.210 --> 00:00:50.030 align:middle line:84%
a part of the curriculum
of medical schools.

00:00:50.030 --> 00:00:52.100 align:middle line:84%
And he is here
joining us to talk

00:00:52.100 --> 00:00:56.440 align:middle line:84%
about the past, the present,
and the future of healing

00:00:56.440 --> 00:00:57.120 align:middle line:90%
and medicine.

00:00:57.120 --> 00:00:58.230 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to the show.

00:00:58.230 --> 00:00:59.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LARRY DOSSEY:
Great to be here.

00:00:59.040 --> 00:00:59.260 align:middle line:90%
Thanks, Lisa.

00:00:59.260 --> 00:01:00.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Thanks for joining me.

00:01:00.040 --> 00:01:01.560 align:middle line:90%
So take us back to your days.

00:01:01.560 --> 00:01:04.849 align:middle line:84%
Now your book is now in its
20th year, which is amazing.

00:01:04.849 --> 00:01:07.450 align:middle line:84%
Take me back to your
early days in medicine

00:01:07.450 --> 00:01:11.540 align:middle line:84%
when you were talking
about prayer 20 years ago

00:01:11.540 --> 00:01:12.504 align:middle line:90%
in medicine.

00:01:12.504 --> 00:01:13.920 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well,
when I first began

00:01:13.920 --> 00:01:16.070 align:middle line:84%
talking about
prayer in medicine,

00:01:16.070 --> 00:01:18.040 align:middle line:84%
this was not
exactly the best way

00:01:18.040 --> 00:01:20.830 align:middle line:84%
to advance your
career in medicine.

00:01:20.830 --> 00:01:23.060 align:middle line:84%
Because it just
wasn't on the menu.

00:01:23.060 --> 00:01:26.350 align:middle line:84%
It suggested something that
was absolutely outrageous,

00:01:26.350 --> 00:01:30.720 align:middle line:84%
that by praying or adopting
healing intentions,

00:01:30.720 --> 00:01:33.560 align:middle line:84%
you could affect
somebody at a distance

00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.730 align:middle line:84%
when they didn't even
know you were doing this.

00:01:36.730 --> 00:01:39.690 align:middle line:84%
And so this just-- there
was no place for this.

00:01:39.690 --> 00:01:41.860 align:middle line:84%
But there was
something that happened

00:01:41.860 --> 00:01:43.980 align:middle line:90%
that made all the difference.

00:01:43.980 --> 00:01:48.050 align:middle line:84%
And it has to do with that
little four letter word-- data.

00:01:48.050 --> 00:01:49.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Ah, yes.

00:01:49.040 --> 00:01:51.030 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Because
back in the 1980s,

00:01:51.030 --> 00:01:54.550 align:middle line:84%
people began to put
this idea to the test.

00:01:54.550 --> 00:01:58.780 align:middle line:84%
And I will never forget in 1988
when a study was published out

00:01:58.780 --> 00:02:01.640 align:middle line:84%
of San Francisco
General Hospital looking

00:02:01.640 --> 00:02:05.950 align:middle line:84%
at the ability of prayer to
make a difference in almost

00:02:05.950 --> 00:02:08.370 align:middle line:90%
400 patients with heart attack.

00:02:08.370 --> 00:02:10.590 align:middle line:84%
And the prayed-for
group did better.

00:02:10.590 --> 00:02:12.300 align:middle line:90%
I was shocked by that.

00:02:12.300 --> 00:02:14.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So now, you started
some of these studies.

00:02:14.620 --> 00:02:17.680 align:middle line:84%
You were participating in
many of these studies, right?

00:02:17.680 --> 00:02:21.210 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I am a referee of the
studies, and I analyze them.

00:02:21.210 --> 00:02:22.820 align:middle line:90%
But I'm not a basic researcher.

00:02:22.820 --> 00:02:25.960 align:middle line:84%
So I look at the studies,
try to make sense of them

00:02:25.960 --> 00:02:29.277 align:middle line:84%
and talk about them and explain
them to the professional.

00:02:29.277 --> 00:02:30.110 align:middle line:90%
That's been my task.

00:02:30.110 --> 00:02:32.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you curate them
so that you can bring them

00:02:32.210 --> 00:02:33.160 align:middle line:90%
to the general public.

00:02:33.160 --> 00:02:34.400 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Curator-- I like that.

00:02:34.400 --> 00:02:34.830 align:middle line:90%
That's good.

00:02:34.830 --> 00:02:35.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I like that.

00:02:35.100 --> 00:02:36.570 align:middle line:90%
You're the curator of ideas.

00:02:36.570 --> 00:02:40.100 align:middle line:84%
[BOTH LAUGH] More than
that, I mean, first of all

00:02:40.100 --> 00:02:42.910 align:middle line:90%
let's qualify the word "prayer."

00:02:42.910 --> 00:02:45.750 align:middle line:84%
You're not talking about a
specific religion or a dogma.

00:02:45.750 --> 00:02:48.330 align:middle line:84%
It's just-- what is
prayer in your terms?

00:02:48.330 --> 00:02:51.000 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, in my way
of thinking about prayer,

00:02:51.000 --> 00:02:54.400 align:middle line:84%
it's a communication
with the absolute.

00:02:54.400 --> 00:02:58.110 align:middle line:84%
And the absolute is my
term for God or Goddess

00:02:58.110 --> 00:02:59.665 align:middle line:90%
or Allah or the divine.

00:02:59.665 --> 00:03:01.040 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Whatever
it means to you.

00:03:01.040 --> 00:03:04.220 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Whatever one's
tradition means to them.

00:03:04.220 --> 00:03:07.560 align:middle line:84%
So I go out of my way not to
mention specific connections

00:03:07.560 --> 00:03:08.790 align:middle line:90%
with religion.

00:03:08.790 --> 00:03:11.482 align:middle line:84%
And Lisa, one reason I
do this is because in all

00:03:11.482 --> 00:03:12.940 align:middle line:84%
of the studies that
have been done,

00:03:12.940 --> 00:03:15.940 align:middle line:84%
looking at the ability of
prayer to make a difference,

00:03:15.940 --> 00:03:19.000 align:middle line:84%
there is no evidence that
any one specific religion

00:03:19.000 --> 00:03:20.417 align:middle line:84%
has cornered the
market on prayer.

00:03:20.417 --> 00:03:21.416 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, interesting.

00:03:21.416 --> 00:03:22.080 align:middle line:90%
Right.

00:03:22.080 --> 00:03:24.550 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So I
like this finding.

00:03:24.550 --> 00:03:26.870 align:middle line:84%
Because it suggests
that we really

00:03:26.870 --> 00:03:30.220 align:middle line:84%
have to be tolerant of a great
variety of religious paths

00:03:30.220 --> 00:03:31.520 align:middle line:90%
and spiritual traditions.

00:03:31.520 --> 00:03:33.644 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So why do you use
the word "prayer" instead

00:03:33.644 --> 00:03:37.160 align:middle line:84%
of "intention" or
"visualization" or "focus?"

00:03:37.160 --> 00:03:44.270 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I find that
in America, where 90% of women

00:03:44.270 --> 00:03:49.420 align:middle line:84%
pray regularly and about 80% of
men, people understand prayer.

00:03:49.420 --> 00:03:52.040 align:middle line:84%
But if I were to go off talking
about "healing intentions,"

00:03:52.040 --> 00:03:53.200 align:middle line:90%
they would say, what?

00:03:53.200 --> 00:03:53.543 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What is that?

00:03:53.543 --> 00:03:53.886 align:middle line:90%
OK, I see.

00:03:53.886 --> 00:03:54.844 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: What is that?

00:03:54.844 --> 00:03:56.937 align:middle line:84%
So I just like to
talk in a language

00:03:56.937 --> 00:03:57.895 align:middle line:90%
that people understand.

00:03:57.895 --> 00:04:00.649 align:middle line:84%
And certainly people
understand-- in America,

00:04:00.649 --> 00:04:01.940 align:middle line:90%
they understand what prayer is.

00:04:01.940 --> 00:04:02.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That is true.

00:04:02.170 --> 00:04:04.210 align:middle line:84%
I saw a statistic
once come out saying

00:04:04.210 --> 00:04:09.107 align:middle line:84%
some over 80% of people
in America believe in God.

00:04:09.107 --> 00:04:10.940 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: No, that's a
good statistic, yeah.

00:04:10.940 --> 00:04:12.981 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, that's
something you found as well.

00:04:12.981 --> 00:04:15.030 align:middle line:84%
So how does-- exactly
how does this work?

00:04:15.030 --> 00:04:20.209 align:middle line:84%
How does the power of prayer
effect lowering blood pressure,

00:04:20.209 --> 00:04:22.900 align:middle line:84%
speeding up recovery
times after surgery,

00:04:22.900 --> 00:04:25.390 align:middle line:84%
lowering the incidence
of heart attacks?

00:04:25.390 --> 00:04:26.797 align:middle line:90%
How does that work?

00:04:26.797 --> 00:04:28.380 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: There are
several mechanisms

00:04:28.380 --> 00:04:29.970 align:middle line:90%
that have been proposed.

00:04:29.970 --> 00:04:34.780 align:middle line:84%
One is just a simple
relaxation and feeling calm.

00:04:34.780 --> 00:04:37.900 align:middle line:84%
People who enter into a
state of prayer or meditation

00:04:37.900 --> 00:04:42.450 align:middle line:84%
have long been known to have
good physiological responses

00:04:42.450 --> 00:04:42.950 align:middle line:90%
to that.

00:04:42.950 --> 00:04:44.830 align:middle line:90%
The blood pressure goes down.

00:04:44.830 --> 00:04:46.890 align:middle line:90%
Respirations tend to diminish.

00:04:46.890 --> 00:04:49.860 align:middle line:90%
Oxygen demand goes down.

00:04:49.860 --> 00:04:51.450 align:middle line:90%
Heart rate tends to fall.

00:04:51.450 --> 00:04:53.710 align:middle line:84%
So these are some of
the things that we've

00:04:53.710 --> 00:04:56.490 align:middle line:84%
known for a long time
about how prayer benefits

00:04:56.490 --> 00:04:58.320 align:middle line:90%
the person who's praying.

00:04:58.320 --> 00:04:59.830 align:middle line:84%
Now the interesting
question comes

00:04:59.830 --> 00:05:02.190 align:middle line:84%
when you inquire
about how prayer

00:05:02.190 --> 00:05:04.955 align:middle line:84%
might affect somebody
else at a distance.

00:05:04.955 --> 00:05:06.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, that's
what it does to you.

00:05:06.580 --> 00:05:07.080 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:05:07.080 --> 00:05:07.720 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Yes.

00:05:07.720 --> 00:05:12.190 align:middle line:84%
And so there are many theories
about how this sort of thing

00:05:12.190 --> 00:05:13.600 align:middle line:90%
can work.

00:05:13.600 --> 00:05:16.550 align:middle line:84%
I think it's only fair to say
that no one knows currently

00:05:16.550 --> 00:05:19.390 align:middle line:84%
what the explanation
will turn out to be.

00:05:19.390 --> 00:05:24.460 align:middle line:84%
The going popular notion is
that people are entangled.

00:05:24.460 --> 00:05:27.160 align:middle line:84%
This is a concept that comes
from quantum mechanics.

00:05:27.160 --> 00:05:31.650 align:middle line:84%
And even though things seem to
be divided and separate and far

00:05:31.650 --> 00:05:33.960 align:middle line:84%
apart, quantum
physics gives us a way

00:05:33.960 --> 00:05:38.200 align:middle line:84%
of understanding how things can
be separate and at a distance

00:05:38.200 --> 00:05:41.800 align:middle line:84%
yet behave as if
they are united.

00:05:41.800 --> 00:05:45.057 align:middle line:84%
The pop word is
"entanglement" in physics.

00:05:45.057 --> 00:05:46.890 align:middle line:84%
Let me add, though,
that whether or not this

00:05:46.890 --> 00:05:50.090 align:middle line:84%
is going to prove to be
the explanation for prayer

00:05:50.090 --> 00:05:51.890 align:middle line:90%
is really up in the air.

00:05:51.890 --> 00:05:54.300 align:middle line:84%
It's just popular,
but we'll have

00:05:54.300 --> 00:05:56.050 align:middle line:84%
to see what idea
floats to the top.

00:05:56.050 --> 00:05:57.549 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, we're
going to explore

00:05:57.549 --> 00:05:59.350 align:middle line:84%
all those today and
all sorts of theories

00:05:59.350 --> 00:06:00.636 align:middle line:90%
of entanglement and studies.

00:06:00.636 --> 00:06:02.010 align:middle line:84%
And that's what
we're doing today

00:06:02.010 --> 00:06:05.320 align:middle line:84%
is bridging that gap between the
science and the spirituality.

00:06:05.320 --> 00:06:08.440 align:middle line:84%
So now, back when you
were practicing-- well,

00:06:08.440 --> 00:06:10.310 align:middle line:84%
when you originally
wrote this book,

00:06:10.310 --> 00:06:12.890 align:middle line:84%
there was a different era in
medicine back then, right?

00:06:12.890 --> 00:06:16.160 align:middle line:84%
There was more of a
conventional era in medicine.

00:06:16.160 --> 00:06:18.740 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Yeah, this
idea that doctors

00:06:18.740 --> 00:06:21.570 align:middle line:84%
ought to explore using
prayer or healing

00:06:21.570 --> 00:06:23.050 align:middle line:84%
intentions with
their own patients

00:06:23.050 --> 00:06:25.850 align:middle line:84%
was considered
heresy and blasphemy.

00:06:25.850 --> 00:06:30.700 align:middle line:84%
I've actually known doctors--
I have a long list of doctors

00:06:30.700 --> 00:06:33.220 align:middle line:84%
who have told me that
they had their hospital

00:06:33.220 --> 00:06:37.290 align:middle line:84%
privileges threatened to be
revoked because they were

00:06:37.290 --> 00:06:39.791 align:middle line:84%
caught praying with a
patient at the bedside.

00:06:39.791 --> 00:06:40.790 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: You are kidding.

00:06:40.790 --> 00:06:41.810 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: No, I'm not.

00:06:41.810 --> 00:06:42.309 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:06:42.309 --> 00:06:44.010 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I think
people today really

00:06:44.010 --> 00:06:47.400 align:middle line:84%
underestimate how controversial
this stuff was back

00:06:47.400 --> 00:06:50.550 align:middle line:84%
in the '50s, '60s,
'70s, and so on.

00:06:50.550 --> 00:06:52.470 align:middle line:84%
Now it's sort of in the
air and in the water.

00:06:52.470 --> 00:06:56.060 align:middle line:84%
People don't really
raise an eyebrow

00:06:56.060 --> 00:06:57.220 align:middle line:90%
over this kind of thing.

00:06:57.220 --> 00:06:59.690 align:middle line:84%
But it wasn't too long
ago where this was not so.

00:06:59.690 --> 00:07:01.440 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, that was
the kind of the Era

00:07:01.440 --> 00:07:03.880 align:middle line:90%
I of medicine, so to speak.

00:07:03.880 --> 00:07:06.420 align:middle line:84%
And then there
there's another era,

00:07:06.420 --> 00:07:08.770 align:middle line:84%
as you've graduated
through the last 20

00:07:08.770 --> 00:07:10.920 align:middle line:90%
years, Era II of medicine.

00:07:10.920 --> 00:07:11.550 align:middle line:90%
What is that?

00:07:11.550 --> 00:07:12.550 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Right.

00:07:12.550 --> 00:07:15.810 align:middle line:84%
Well, I use Era I to designate
the mechanical approach

00:07:15.810 --> 00:07:19.950 align:middle line:84%
to things such as the use of
drugs and surgical procedures.

00:07:19.950 --> 00:07:21.720 align:middle line:90%
Those are very mechanical.

00:07:21.720 --> 00:07:25.130 align:middle line:84%
But then around World War II,
shortly thereafter, Era II

00:07:25.130 --> 00:07:26.300 align:middle line:90%
came on board.

00:07:26.300 --> 00:07:28.690 align:middle line:90%
And that's mind-body medicine.

00:07:28.690 --> 00:07:32.800 align:middle line:84%
And today, people adapt
to this quite naturally.

00:07:32.800 --> 00:07:34.960 align:middle line:84%
Everybody's enrolled
in a meditation or yoga

00:07:34.960 --> 00:07:36.030 align:middle line:90%
class it seems.

00:07:36.030 --> 00:07:38.810 align:middle line:84%
And imagery and
visualization are

00:07:38.810 --> 00:07:41.550 align:middle line:84%
accepted as pretty
important aspects of--

00:07:41.550 --> 00:07:43.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Around what
decade was that?

00:07:43.340 --> 00:07:45.980 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: The late
1940s and early 1950s.

00:07:45.980 --> 00:07:47.994 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:07:47.994 --> 00:07:49.660 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: But these
things in those days

00:07:49.660 --> 00:07:52.475 align:middle line:84%
were indeed also
very controversial.

00:07:52.475 --> 00:07:53.850 align:middle line:84%
But now they've
just sort of been

00:07:53.850 --> 00:07:57.650 align:middle line:84%
incorporated into
conventional medicine.

00:07:57.650 --> 00:07:59.790 align:middle line:84%
The exciting thing
is where we begin

00:07:59.790 --> 00:08:03.530 align:middle line:84%
to talk about prayer and
distant intentions and so on.

00:08:03.530 --> 00:08:05.180 align:middle line:84%
And that gets us
into what I call

00:08:05.180 --> 00:08:08.690 align:middle line:84%
Era III, or non-local
medicine, which we'll discuss.

00:08:08.690 --> 00:08:11.230 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well the Era III
Medicine is what we're in now.

00:08:11.230 --> 00:08:14.910 align:middle line:84%
This is why your book is able
to come out and be a number one

00:08:14.910 --> 00:08:18.760 align:middle line:84%
bestseller for-- when it
was originally released.

00:08:18.760 --> 00:08:21.021 align:middle line:84%
And it stayed on the bestseller
list for a long time.

00:08:21.021 --> 00:08:22.395 align:middle line:84%
Actually, you have
a little story

00:08:22.395 --> 00:08:25.420 align:middle line:84%
you told us about that,
which was fascinating to me,

00:08:25.420 --> 00:08:26.880 align:middle line:90%
about the book.

00:08:26.880 --> 00:08:29.370 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I had
written a couple of books

00:08:29.370 --> 00:08:33.000 align:middle line:84%
about the role of
consciousness in health.

00:08:33.000 --> 00:08:38.480 align:middle line:84%
And so these were published
without too much indigestion

00:08:38.480 --> 00:08:39.799 align:middle line:90%
by my publisher.

00:08:39.799 --> 00:08:42.789 align:middle line:84%
But when I presented them
with the book on prayer,

00:08:42.789 --> 00:08:44.310 align:middle line:90%
they refused to publish it.

00:08:44.310 --> 00:08:49.060 align:middle line:84%
And the reasoning was that you
can't sell a book on prayer.

00:08:49.060 --> 00:08:52.880 align:middle line:84%
There's no connection between
prayer and healing and science.

00:08:52.880 --> 00:08:54.860 align:middle line:90%
The whole idea is crazy.

00:08:54.860 --> 00:08:57.912 align:middle line:84%
So I wound up overnight
without a publisher.

00:08:57.912 --> 00:08:59.620 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Because they
wouldn't publish it.

00:08:59.620 --> 00:09:00.290 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: No.

00:09:00.290 --> 00:09:02.850 align:middle line:84%
They thought it was
an idiotic theme,

00:09:02.850 --> 00:09:04.125 align:middle line:90%
the arguments were crazy.

00:09:04.125 --> 00:09:05.750 align:middle line:84%
They weren't interested
in the science,

00:09:05.750 --> 00:09:08.080 align:middle line:84%
even though the
science was there,

00:09:08.080 --> 00:09:10.150 align:middle line:84%
even randomized
controlled studies.

00:09:10.150 --> 00:09:14.830 align:middle line:90%
This was just off the table.

00:09:14.830 --> 00:09:20.040 align:middle line:84%
So I wound up finding a
blessed, open-minded publisher

00:09:20.040 --> 00:09:21.004 align:middle line:90%
to publish the book.

00:09:21.004 --> 00:09:21.920 align:middle line:90%
And they published it.

00:09:21.920 --> 00:09:24.750 align:middle line:84%
And as you mentioned--
thank you--

00:09:24.750 --> 00:09:27.240 align:middle line:84%
it wound up on the New
York Times Bestseller List.

00:09:27.240 --> 00:09:29.960 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, and the rest
is history on that one.

00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:35.370 align:middle line:84%
So what is what you consider
the definition of spirituality

00:09:35.370 --> 00:09:36.580 align:middle line:90%
in medicine?

00:09:36.580 --> 00:09:39.090 align:middle line:90%
How does that translate?

00:09:39.090 --> 00:09:41.290 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I think
a definition that

00:09:41.290 --> 00:09:43.390 align:middle line:84%
would go down pretty
easily for most people is

00:09:43.390 --> 00:09:46.990 align:middle line:84%
that spirituality is a sense of
being connected with something

00:09:46.990 --> 00:09:48.840 align:middle line:84%
greater than the
individual self.

00:09:48.840 --> 00:09:49.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:09:49.820 --> 00:09:53.250 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Whether that
transcendent being is something

00:09:53.250 --> 00:09:56.270 align:middle line:84%
people want to call God or
Goddess or Allah or the Divine

00:09:56.270 --> 00:09:57.680 align:middle line:90%
or whatever.

00:09:57.680 --> 00:10:00.075 align:middle line:84%
But it's different
from religion.

00:10:00.075 --> 00:10:01.033 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's different.

00:10:01.033 --> 00:10:02.190 align:middle line:90%
OK.

00:10:02.190 --> 00:10:05.210 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Religion tends to
be a codified system of belief

00:10:05.210 --> 00:10:09.380 align:middle line:84%
and behavior that people
engage in in a congregation.

00:10:09.380 --> 00:10:12.940 align:middle line:84%
They come together with
people of like-minded belief.

00:10:12.940 --> 00:10:17.580 align:middle line:84%
And I think people
can be spiritual

00:10:17.580 --> 00:10:19.710 align:middle line:90%
without being religious.

00:10:19.710 --> 00:10:21.620 align:middle line:84%
I think I know a
lot of people who

00:10:21.620 --> 00:10:23.190 align:middle line:84%
are religious who
don't seem to have

00:10:23.190 --> 00:10:25.070 align:middle line:90%
much spirituality about them.

00:10:25.070 --> 00:10:27.610 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It would be interesting
to see the trends on that,

00:10:27.610 --> 00:10:28.720 align:middle line:90%
how that is trending now.

00:10:28.720 --> 00:10:30.770 align:middle line:84%
I've spoken with
many, many guests that

00:10:30.770 --> 00:10:33.520 align:middle line:84%
have said the same thing,
that there is a drifting away,

00:10:33.520 --> 00:10:35.910 align:middle line:84%
especially with young
children, of teaching

00:10:35.910 --> 00:10:39.280 align:middle line:84%
them the organized religion
that they were raised with

00:10:39.280 --> 00:10:43.560 align:middle line:84%
and raising them with more of
a moralistic, spiritual concept

00:10:43.560 --> 00:10:46.550 align:middle line:90%
around the face of morality.

00:10:46.550 --> 00:10:48.120 align:middle line:90%
And I am the same way.

00:10:48.120 --> 00:10:49.320 align:middle line:90%
I do the same thing.

00:10:49.320 --> 00:10:50.720 align:middle line:90%
I have a young child.

00:10:50.720 --> 00:10:52.600 align:middle line:84%
And so we're raising
her with what

00:10:52.600 --> 00:10:55.696 align:middle line:84%
it means to be a good
person and also God.

00:10:55.696 --> 00:10:57.070 align:middle line:84%
And there's concepts
around then.

00:10:57.070 --> 00:10:58.945 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of people
doing the same thing,

00:10:58.945 --> 00:11:01.864 align:middle line:84%
yet there's also a lot of people
in organized religion as well.

00:11:01.864 --> 00:11:03.030 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Well, that's true.

00:11:03.030 --> 00:11:04.904 align:middle line:84%
And I think it's important
to say that people

00:11:04.904 --> 00:11:08.520 align:middle line:84%
can be religious and spiritual,
and spiritual and religious.

00:11:08.520 --> 00:11:10.660 align:middle line:84%
So we don't want to put
these things in a box

00:11:10.660 --> 00:11:12.260 align:middle line:90%
and say you can't be both.

00:11:12.260 --> 00:11:14.460 align:middle line:90%
A lot of people are both.

00:11:14.460 --> 00:11:18.640 align:middle line:84%
This is important, because if
you look at the studies looking

00:11:18.640 --> 00:11:23.530 align:middle line:84%
at people's intentions
to heal someone else,

00:11:23.530 --> 00:11:26.547 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't matter
what you call it.

00:11:26.547 --> 00:11:27.130 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's

00:11:27.130 --> 00:11:28.250 align:middle line:90%
true.

00:11:28.250 --> 00:11:29.830 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Whether
you use a language

00:11:29.830 --> 00:11:35.290 align:middle line:84%
that involves "thee" and "thou"
or whether you pray to God

00:11:35.290 --> 00:11:37.390 align:middle line:84%
or whether you don't
consider yourself

00:11:37.390 --> 00:11:40.210 align:middle line:84%
affiliated with a religion
at all, a lot of the studies

00:11:40.210 --> 00:11:42.270 align:middle line:84%
show that people
who are absolutely

00:11:42.270 --> 00:11:45.490 align:middle line:84%
unaffiliated with religion
can achieve success

00:11:45.490 --> 00:11:47.250 align:middle line:90%
in these healing studies.

00:11:47.250 --> 00:11:49.590 align:middle line:84%
So we come back again
and again to the idea

00:11:49.590 --> 00:11:54.410 align:middle line:84%
that no specific religion has
a monopoly on these healing

00:11:54.410 --> 00:11:56.230 align:middle line:90%
intentions or prayer.

00:11:56.230 --> 00:11:58.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So if no
specific religion

00:11:58.200 --> 00:12:00.760 align:middle line:84%
has the monopoly on
it, and spirituality

00:12:00.760 --> 00:12:05.150 align:middle line:84%
is an overarching theme
around it, the way that you

00:12:05.150 --> 00:12:07.970 align:middle line:84%
have quantified that this
actually affects people,

00:12:07.970 --> 00:12:10.350 align:middle line:84%
in your practice for example,
give me an example of,

00:12:10.350 --> 00:12:12.970 align:middle line:84%
in your practice,
how this had worked.

00:12:12.970 --> 00:12:15.730 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, the first
example that comes to mind

00:12:15.730 --> 00:12:19.840 align:middle line:84%
is an experience I had
during my medical training

00:12:19.840 --> 00:12:21.490 align:middle line:90%
in internal medicine.

00:12:21.490 --> 00:12:23.580 align:middle line:84%
I had a patient in
the hospital who

00:12:23.580 --> 00:12:26.640 align:middle line:84%
was an elderly man who
was a heavy smoker.

00:12:26.640 --> 00:12:27.990 align:middle line:90%
He was in his 80s.

00:12:27.990 --> 00:12:30.940 align:middle line:84%
And he had metastatic
lung cancer.

00:12:30.940 --> 00:12:33.020 align:middle line:84%
There was nothing
to be done for this.

00:12:33.020 --> 00:12:35.550 align:middle line:84%
He opted to have no
therapy, which was smart,

00:12:35.550 --> 00:12:38.440 align:middle line:84%
because no therapy worked in
those days for this problem.

00:12:38.440 --> 00:12:41.360 align:middle line:84%
The only therapy he had, if
you want to call it a therapy,

00:12:41.360 --> 00:12:43.440 align:middle line:84%
is that the congregation
from his church

00:12:43.440 --> 00:12:47.290 align:middle line:84%
came and ringed his bedside
at all visiting hours

00:12:47.290 --> 00:12:50.040 align:middle line:90%
and prayed nonstop for this guy.

00:12:50.040 --> 00:12:53.040 align:middle line:84%
Well, at that time in my life,
I was not impressed by this.

00:12:53.040 --> 00:12:55.800 align:middle line:90%
He wanted to go home to die.

00:12:55.800 --> 00:12:59.800 align:middle line:84%
And so I discharged
him at his wish.

00:12:59.800 --> 00:13:02.350 align:middle line:84%
And a year later, he showed
back up at the hospital

00:13:02.350 --> 00:13:04.210 align:middle line:90%
with a bad case of the flu.

00:13:04.210 --> 00:13:05.900 align:middle line:84%
I did another
chest x-ray on him,

00:13:05.900 --> 00:13:07.800 align:middle line:90%
and it was perfectly clear.

00:13:07.800 --> 00:13:12.710 align:middle line:84%
This man recovered from
metastatic, lethal lung cancer,

00:13:12.710 --> 00:13:16.500 align:middle line:84%
and the only therapy that he
was exposed to was prayer.

00:13:16.500 --> 00:13:18.120 align:middle line:90%
This really got my attention.

00:13:18.120 --> 00:13:19.170 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: As his doctor.

00:13:19.170 --> 00:13:20.310 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: As his physician.

00:13:20.310 --> 00:13:21.768 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know what
to do with this.

00:13:21.768 --> 00:13:27.330 align:middle line:84%
So I repressed it, you know,
things you can't figure out

00:13:27.330 --> 00:13:30.140 align:middle line:84%
and you get sort of
messed around about,

00:13:30.140 --> 00:13:32.470 align:middle line:90%
you just sort of deny them.

00:13:32.470 --> 00:13:34.164 align:middle line:90%
I'm good at denial.

00:13:34.164 --> 00:13:35.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, as
a physician, when

00:13:35.580 --> 00:13:38.600 align:middle line:84%
your world is about science,
I'm sure a lot of other doctors

00:13:38.600 --> 00:13:40.850 align:middle line:84%
are in that same-- they don't
know what to do with it.

00:13:40.850 --> 00:13:42.120 align:middle line:90%
It can't be quantified.

00:13:42.120 --> 00:13:44.462 align:middle line:84%
This was a spontaneous
remission, and dismiss it.

00:13:44.462 --> 00:13:45.670 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Well, that's right.

00:13:45.670 --> 00:13:47.060 align:middle line:90%
That's what I did.

00:13:47.060 --> 00:13:50.600 align:middle line:84%
And years later, the thing
that really got my attention,

00:13:50.600 --> 00:13:53.220 align:middle line:84%
as I've already mentioned,
are the randomized controlled

00:13:53.220 --> 00:13:54.800 align:middle line:84%
studies on prayer
and healing that

00:13:54.800 --> 00:13:59.870 align:middle line:84%
began to be done in a serious
way in modern hospitals.

00:13:59.870 --> 00:14:02.490 align:middle line:84%
I mentioned one that was
done at San Francisco General

00:14:02.490 --> 00:14:04.660 align:middle line:84%
Hospital in the
Coronary Care Unit.

00:14:04.660 --> 00:14:07.440 align:middle line:84%
At that time, I had patients
in the Coronary Care Unit

00:14:07.440 --> 00:14:08.970 align:middle line:90%
at all times.

00:14:08.970 --> 00:14:10.330 align:middle line:90%
And so here's what I thought.

00:14:10.330 --> 00:14:13.870 align:middle line:84%
I thought, if there's
anything to this controlled,

00:14:13.870 --> 00:14:15.910 align:middle line:84%
double-blind study
showing that prayer seems

00:14:15.910 --> 00:14:20.850 align:middle line:84%
to work in coronary patients,
and I'm not doing it,

00:14:20.850 --> 00:14:22.440 align:middle line:90%
do I have a problem with that?

00:14:22.440 --> 00:14:25.070 align:middle line:84%
I mean, am I denying
my patients something

00:14:25.070 --> 00:14:26.450 align:middle line:90%
that might be helpful?

00:14:26.450 --> 00:14:29.260 align:middle line:84%
And I got really
concerned about that.

00:14:29.260 --> 00:14:31.420 align:middle line:84%
The way of resolving
that crisis for me

00:14:31.420 --> 00:14:34.480 align:middle line:84%
was to look at the
world's literature, trying

00:14:34.480 --> 00:14:37.610 align:middle line:84%
to find other studies
that had to do with this.

00:14:37.610 --> 00:14:39.770 align:middle line:84%
I thought I might uncover
two or three extra ones

00:14:39.770 --> 00:14:41.250 align:middle line:90%
that I hadn't heard about.

00:14:41.250 --> 00:14:42.850 align:middle line:90%
I came up with 130.

00:14:42.850 --> 00:14:49.020 align:middle line:84%
And 2/3 of them show that there
is a positive effect from this.

00:14:49.020 --> 00:14:51.290 align:middle line:84%
I began to think this
is the best kept secret

00:14:51.290 --> 00:14:53.110 align:middle line:90%
in modern medicine.

00:14:53.110 --> 00:14:56.740 align:middle line:84%
And so I began to adapt
prayer for all my patients.

00:14:56.740 --> 00:15:00.160 align:middle line:84%
And that's how the book
got published, by the way,

00:15:00.160 --> 00:15:04.500 align:middle line:84%
and written, looking at
the data, not just stories,

00:15:04.500 --> 00:15:07.000 align:middle line:84%
not just anecdotes,
but combining

00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:09.980 align:middle line:84%
the scientific research
with the stories.

00:15:09.980 --> 00:15:12.800 align:middle line:84%
And that's how "Healing
Words" came to be.

00:15:12.800 --> 00:15:16.425 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And did you pray at
the bedside of these patients?

00:15:16.425 --> 00:15:19.021 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I invented my
own private prayer ritual.

00:15:19.021 --> 00:15:19.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:15:19.520 --> 00:15:22.580 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I would go into my
office early in the morning,

00:15:22.580 --> 00:15:24.920 align:middle line:84%
earlier than usual,
close my door,

00:15:24.920 --> 00:15:30.260 align:middle line:84%
and have my own private
prayer ritual that I invented.

00:15:30.260 --> 00:15:31.217 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Which was?

00:15:31.217 --> 00:15:33.050 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Oh, well, you
really want to know?

00:15:33.050 --> 00:15:33.591 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I do.

00:15:33.591 --> 00:15:34.970 align:middle line:90%
Yes, yes.

00:15:34.970 --> 00:15:37.360 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, over
the years, my patients

00:15:37.360 --> 00:15:40.920 align:middle line:84%
knew I was interested in
the anthropology of healing.

00:15:40.920 --> 00:15:44.360 align:middle line:84%
And so they had
given me as gifts

00:15:44.360 --> 00:15:47.990 align:middle line:84%
various shamanic rattles
and various herbal incenses

00:15:47.990 --> 00:15:49.340 align:middle line:90%
from around the world.

00:15:49.340 --> 00:15:52.700 align:middle line:84%
And so I concocted
my own ritual where

00:15:52.700 --> 00:15:56.830 align:middle line:84%
I would burn incense that
shamans and healers were using

00:15:56.830 --> 00:15:59.190 align:middle line:84%
around the world
and shake my rattles

00:15:59.190 --> 00:16:03.490 align:middle line:84%
and say my healing request
and prayers for my patients

00:16:03.490 --> 00:16:06.790 align:middle line:84%
that I would be seeing on
hospital rounds that morning

00:16:06.790 --> 00:16:08.990 align:middle line:84%
and who would be coming
to my office that day.

00:16:08.990 --> 00:16:12.880 align:middle line:84%
And I continued
this ritual until I

00:16:12.880 --> 00:16:15.620 align:middle line:84%
retired from the practice
of internal medicine.

00:16:15.620 --> 00:16:18.030 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That blows my mind.

00:16:18.030 --> 00:16:19.980 align:middle line:84%
What was it like when
you were in the office?

00:16:19.980 --> 00:16:21.650 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Dossey's in, and
here's the rattles

00:16:21.650 --> 00:16:23.339 align:middle line:90%
and-- and you got the-- [LAUGHS]

00:16:23.339 --> 00:16:25.130 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, actually
I went in so early

00:16:25.130 --> 00:16:26.754 align:middle line:84%
that I was about the
only person there.

00:16:26.754 --> 00:16:28.966 align:middle line:84%
I was not likely
to be interrupted.

00:16:28.966 --> 00:16:30.840 align:middle line:84%
But I will tell you an
interesting experience

00:16:30.840 --> 00:16:32.170 align:middle line:90%
along those lines.

00:16:32.170 --> 00:16:35.280 align:middle line:84%
One morning I burned too
much incense in my ritual,

00:16:35.280 --> 00:16:37.070 align:middle line:90%
and the smoke alarm went off.

00:16:37.070 --> 00:16:39.260 align:middle line:84%
And I was paid a visit
by the fire inspector

00:16:39.260 --> 00:16:43.380 align:middle line:84%
of the hospital who wanted to
know what that funny smell was.

00:16:43.380 --> 00:16:48.150 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, no. [LAUGHS] Well,
my father was a physician.

00:16:48.150 --> 00:16:50.510 align:middle line:84%
And I remember he
would go into rounds,

00:16:50.510 --> 00:16:53.070 align:middle line:84%
and he would sometimes
dread going into the rounds.

00:16:53.070 --> 00:16:54.794 align:middle line:90%
And it would take a lot of time.

00:16:54.794 --> 00:16:57.460 align:middle line:84%
But he would spend a lot of time
with his patients and so forth.

00:16:57.460 --> 00:17:01.130 align:middle line:84%
But never once do I think he
went in and burned sage and did

00:17:01.130 --> 00:17:03.150 align:middle line:90%
the shamanic ritual.

00:17:03.150 --> 00:17:04.599 align:middle line:90%
Did it work?

00:17:04.599 --> 00:17:08.210 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I am
convinced that it did.

00:17:08.210 --> 00:17:10.890 align:middle line:84%
I didn't make a public
to-do about this.

00:17:10.890 --> 00:17:14.550 align:middle line:84%
Because one never knows
precisely where your patients

00:17:14.550 --> 00:17:18.859 align:middle line:84%
are religiously or spiritually,
and because I was positive

00:17:18.859 --> 00:17:20.880 align:middle line:84%
that prayer could
work at a distance.

00:17:20.880 --> 00:17:23.089 align:middle line:84%
I felt pretty confident
doing this in solitude

00:17:23.089 --> 00:17:27.099 align:middle line:84%
in the privacy of my own office
on behalf of my patients.

00:17:27.099 --> 00:17:30.910 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it must
have, in some way-- did

00:17:30.910 --> 00:17:32.760 align:middle line:84%
you want to quantify
it in some way?

00:17:32.760 --> 00:17:35.760 align:middle line:84%
Did you ever see the patients
that you prayed for more?

00:17:35.760 --> 00:17:37.150 align:middle line:90%
Because you read the studies.

00:17:37.150 --> 00:17:38.220 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I did.

00:17:38.220 --> 00:17:41.540 align:middle line:84%
You know, those studies
are done more easily

00:17:41.540 --> 00:17:44.780 align:middle line:84%
in academic environments where
one has a huge staff that

00:17:44.780 --> 00:17:49.400 align:middle line:84%
can be involved in
gathering data and so on.

00:17:49.400 --> 00:17:51.000 align:middle line:84%
It's very difficult
to do that just

00:17:51.000 --> 00:17:54.180 align:middle line:84%
in a single doctor's
private practice.

00:17:54.180 --> 00:17:55.890 align:middle line:84%
I knew most of the
people who were

00:17:55.890 --> 00:17:59.340 align:middle line:84%
doing the research,
however, by that time.

00:17:59.340 --> 00:18:01.932 align:middle line:84%
And I had great confidence
in their ability to do that.

00:18:01.932 --> 00:18:03.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's amazing,
though, because now there

00:18:03.890 --> 00:18:08.339 align:middle line:84%
are so many more doctors
who are alternative.

00:18:08.339 --> 00:18:10.380 align:middle line:84%
I guess I can't even use
the word "alternative"--

00:18:10.380 --> 00:18:11.410 align:middle line:90%
integrative.

00:18:11.410 --> 00:18:14.990 align:middle line:84%
And this is definitely a
rising trend in medicine.

00:18:14.990 --> 00:18:17.220 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Andrew Weil says it's
the future of medicine.

00:18:17.220 --> 00:18:19.800 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure you do as well,
integrative medicine.

00:18:19.800 --> 00:18:22.650 align:middle line:84%
And that is what you
were doing 20 years ago.

00:18:22.650 --> 00:18:24.080 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's right.

00:18:24.080 --> 00:18:26.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I recently read
that there are actually

00:18:26.860 --> 00:18:29.420 align:middle line:84%
more visits to
alternative practitioners

00:18:29.420 --> 00:18:33.050 align:middle line:84%
now than there are to
actual medical doctors.

00:18:33.050 --> 00:18:35.090 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, that's
a valid statistic.

00:18:35.090 --> 00:18:37.250 align:middle line:90%
That's exactly right.

00:18:37.250 --> 00:18:40.920 align:middle line:84%
And I think this is one reason
that the medical schools have

00:18:40.920 --> 00:18:43.380 align:middle line:90%
come on board.

00:18:43.380 --> 00:18:47.840 align:middle line:84%
For one thing, it has to do
with the economics of medicine.

00:18:47.840 --> 00:18:50.870 align:middle line:84%
When more patients are going
to so-called alternative

00:18:50.870 --> 00:18:53.160 align:middle line:84%
practitioners than
conventional doctors,

00:18:53.160 --> 00:18:55.760 align:middle line:84%
that's a lot of money
going out the front door.

00:18:55.760 --> 00:19:01.050 align:middle line:84%
And so doctors have become
interested in this on economics

00:19:01.050 --> 00:19:05.200 align:middle line:84%
alone, in addition to the fact
that these things may actually

00:19:05.200 --> 00:19:06.460 align:middle line:90%
have benefit for patients.

00:19:06.460 --> 00:19:10.025 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Then why isn't
insurance covering it more?

00:19:10.025 --> 00:19:11.650 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: That's a
tremendous question.

00:19:11.650 --> 00:19:14.460 align:middle line:84%
And I think that it is
only a matter of time

00:19:14.460 --> 00:19:17.360 align:middle line:84%
until insurance companies
wake up to the fact

00:19:17.360 --> 00:19:21.630 align:middle line:84%
that these things have economic
payoff for the insurance

00:19:21.630 --> 00:19:23.180 align:middle line:90%
company.

00:19:23.180 --> 00:19:26.090 align:middle line:84%
One reason I say that is that
people who follow some sort

00:19:26.090 --> 00:19:30.680 align:middle line:84%
of spiritual or religious path
in their life live on average 7

00:19:30.680 --> 00:19:33.797 align:middle line:84%
to 13 years longer
than people who don't.

00:19:33.797 --> 00:19:34.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:19:34.630 --> 00:19:35.921 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: And here's the thing.

00:19:35.921 --> 00:19:38.380 align:middle line:84%
This is where the insurance
companies will be looking,

00:19:38.380 --> 00:19:40.080 align:middle line:90%
be paying attention.

00:19:40.080 --> 00:19:44.010 align:middle line:84%
In the process, people
have a lower incidence

00:19:44.010 --> 00:19:46.950 align:middle line:84%
of all the major diseases,
including heart disease

00:19:46.950 --> 00:19:49.350 align:middle line:84%
and cancer, if they
follow some sort

00:19:49.350 --> 00:19:51.415 align:middle line:84%
of spiritual or religious
path in their life.

00:19:51.415 --> 00:19:52.040 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:19:52.040 --> 00:19:53.830 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So the
insurance companies

00:19:53.830 --> 00:19:57.821 align:middle line:84%
have a lot to gain by paying
attention to this kind of data.

00:19:57.821 --> 00:19:59.570 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But it's been
around-- that data's

00:19:59.570 --> 00:20:03.020 align:middle line:84%
been around for 10
years almost now.

00:20:03.020 --> 00:20:04.520 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Actually
longer than that.

00:20:04.520 --> 00:20:05.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Longer than that, yeah.

00:20:05.260 --> 00:20:06.690 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: It's been out there.

00:20:06.690 --> 00:20:08.820 align:middle line:84%
But old habits
are hard to break.

00:20:08.820 --> 00:20:10.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, when the
systems are ingrained.

00:20:10.790 --> 00:20:11.380 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Absolutely.

00:20:11.380 --> 00:20:13.340 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, and
they're big systems, too.

00:20:13.340 --> 00:20:14.170 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:20:14.170 --> 00:20:16.640 align:middle line:84%
Well, so there is a link
between spirituality

00:20:16.640 --> 00:20:19.130 align:middle line:84%
and integrative health care
that you understand, yes.

00:20:19.130 --> 00:20:20.560 align:middle line:90%
And we have a slide about that.

00:20:20.560 --> 00:20:22.860 align:middle line:90%
Explain that, that link.

00:20:22.860 --> 00:20:25.870 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, spirituality
and alternative health care

00:20:25.870 --> 00:20:26.960 align:middle line:90%
do go together.

00:20:26.960 --> 00:20:29.600 align:middle line:90%
And the question is why.

00:20:29.600 --> 00:20:31.530 align:middle line:84%
There are surveys
that show that people

00:20:31.530 --> 00:20:33.810 align:middle line:84%
who choose to go to
so-called alternative

00:20:33.810 --> 00:20:37.670 align:middle line:84%
or complementary or
integrative practitioners

00:20:37.670 --> 00:20:42.330 align:middle line:84%
have had some sort of change
in the way they see the world.

00:20:42.330 --> 00:20:45.340 align:middle line:84%
Many talk about a
transformational experience

00:20:45.340 --> 00:20:47.470 align:middle line:90%
about how they see things.

00:20:47.470 --> 00:20:49.290 align:middle line:90%
They see themselves integrated.

00:20:49.290 --> 00:20:52.400 align:middle line:84%
They see themselves part
of a larger pattern.

00:20:52.400 --> 00:20:54.760 align:middle line:84%
And people, after
having this kind

00:20:54.760 --> 00:20:57.950 align:middle line:84%
of awakening about how
they are in the world,

00:20:57.950 --> 00:21:00.990 align:middle line:84%
are looking for doctors
who represent or are

00:21:00.990 --> 00:21:03.530 align:middle line:84%
cordial to that way
of looking at things.

00:21:03.530 --> 00:21:06.940 align:middle line:84%
And most people who
have this point of view

00:21:06.940 --> 00:21:10.600 align:middle line:84%
see in alternative
therapists a point of view

00:21:10.600 --> 00:21:12.750 align:middle line:84%
that's more compatible
with the way

00:21:12.750 --> 00:21:16.220 align:middle line:84%
they see things and the way they
experience being in the world

00:21:16.220 --> 00:21:19.860 align:middle line:84%
than they see being represented
by conventional doctors who

00:21:19.860 --> 00:21:23.185 align:middle line:84%
use only or mainly drugs
and surgical procedures.

00:21:23.185 --> 00:21:24.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, right.

00:21:24.060 --> 00:21:26.760 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So people sort
of sort themselves out

00:21:26.760 --> 00:21:30.450 align:middle line:84%
with the kind of doctor
that they feel at home with,

00:21:30.450 --> 00:21:31.440 align:middle line:90%
is what it amounts to.

00:21:31.440 --> 00:21:32.023 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:21:32.023 --> 00:21:34.500 align:middle line:84%
And usually the doctor has had
that same type of experience

00:21:34.500 --> 00:21:37.320 align:middle line:84%
where they've had a spiritual
awakening or some type

00:21:37.320 --> 00:21:40.720 align:middle line:84%
of awakening or something that
dawned on them that they need

00:21:40.720 --> 00:21:44.840 align:middle line:84%
to soften that or transition
that level of their practice.

00:21:44.840 --> 00:21:46.900 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that's why
"Healing Words" is now

00:21:46.900 --> 00:21:50.220 align:middle line:84%
used in how many of the medical
schools now as a textbook?

00:21:50.220 --> 00:21:52.740 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, there
are dozens of them.

00:21:52.740 --> 00:21:56.000 align:middle line:84%
A fact I always come back to is
that when the book was written,

00:21:56.000 --> 00:21:58.570 align:middle line:84%
out of the 125 medical
schools in the country,

00:21:58.570 --> 00:22:02.160 align:middle line:84%
only three had any
formal coursework looking

00:22:02.160 --> 00:22:04.770 align:middle line:84%
at the connection between
spirituality and healing.

00:22:04.770 --> 00:22:06.470 align:middle line:84%
And now, since the
book has been out

00:22:06.470 --> 00:22:09.230 align:middle line:84%
and has been used here
and there, over 90

00:22:09.230 --> 00:22:12.300 align:middle line:84%
of the nation's
128 medical schools

00:22:12.300 --> 00:22:17.430 align:middle line:84%
now feature course work looking
at the role of spirituality

00:22:17.430 --> 00:22:18.580 align:middle line:90%
and affecting health care.

00:22:18.580 --> 00:22:20.600 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Spirituality
and alternative.

00:22:20.600 --> 00:22:23.640 align:middle line:84%
And so this has
been definitely--

00:22:23.640 --> 00:22:26.840 align:middle line:84%
there's a slide here that talks
about a survey of physicians.

00:22:26.840 --> 00:22:31.310 align:middle line:84%
And so now doctors are starting
to accept more this concept

00:22:31.310 --> 00:22:36.470 align:middle line:84%
of prayer in-- specifically
prayer and the concept

00:22:36.470 --> 00:22:39.327 align:middle line:84%
of spirituality as an
umbrella in medicine.

00:22:39.327 --> 00:22:41.160 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I'm really
glad you bring this up,

00:22:41.160 --> 00:22:43.840 align:middle line:84%
because when I was going
through medical school,

00:22:43.840 --> 00:22:45.917 align:middle line:84%
I was taught that
good doctors don't

00:22:45.917 --> 00:22:47.000 align:middle line:90%
believe any of this stuff.

00:22:47.000 --> 00:22:47.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, wow.

00:22:47.750 --> 00:22:49.350 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: It's mechanical
stuff all the way.

00:22:49.350 --> 00:22:50.610 align:middle line:84%
It's drugs and
surgical procedures.

00:22:50.610 --> 00:22:51.990 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So it's the opposite.

00:22:51.990 --> 00:22:54.090 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So this is
a myth that doctors

00:22:54.090 --> 00:22:56.440 align:middle line:84%
don't believe in a connection
between spirituality

00:22:56.440 --> 00:22:57.410 align:middle line:90%
and health.

00:22:57.410 --> 00:23:02.130 align:middle line:84%
The surveys show that
3/4 of physicians

00:23:02.130 --> 00:23:09.510 align:middle line:84%
believe in spiritual effects,
even including miracle cures.

00:23:09.510 --> 00:23:11.910 align:middle line:84%
2/3 of them pray
for their patients

00:23:11.910 --> 00:23:15.260 align:middle line:84%
as a group or
individually, thereabouts.

00:23:15.260 --> 00:23:18.230 align:middle line:84%
And so this whole idea that
doctors don't believe anything

00:23:18.230 --> 00:23:20.620 align:middle line:84%
about the role of
spirituality in healing

00:23:20.620 --> 00:23:24.200 align:middle line:84%
is just a myth that really
needs to be put to rest.

00:23:24.200 --> 00:23:28.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it's definitely
above the 50% level.

00:23:28.860 --> 00:23:32.420 align:middle line:84%
This is well into many,
many of these physicians.

00:23:32.420 --> 00:23:34.535 align:middle line:84%
And if physicians
are watching this,

00:23:34.535 --> 00:23:36.710 align:middle line:84%
this helps them
identify with the fact

00:23:36.710 --> 00:23:38.740 align:middle line:84%
that there is--
it's not just them

00:23:38.740 --> 00:23:41.200 align:middle line:84%
who believes in these
types of things.

00:23:41.200 --> 00:23:44.130 align:middle line:84%
I know that there's a lot more
nutritional information now

00:23:44.130 --> 00:23:45.030 align:middle line:90%
in medical schools.

00:23:45.030 --> 00:23:47.910 align:middle line:84%
My father is a medical
doctor, and he has now

00:23:47.910 --> 00:23:51.310 align:middle line:84%
gone back to study nutrition,
because it wasn't there when

00:23:51.310 --> 00:23:53.880 align:middle line:84%
he studied it, and
originally because it's

00:23:53.880 --> 00:23:57.940 align:middle line:84%
more so about the
mind-body-spirit connection.

00:23:57.940 --> 00:24:00.200 align:middle line:90%
It's definitely all altogether.

00:24:00.200 --> 00:24:04.840 align:middle line:84%
So did you at the time--
what type of criticism

00:24:04.840 --> 00:24:08.070 align:middle line:84%
were you experiencing when
you had-- when you brought

00:24:08.070 --> 00:24:11.850 align:middle line:84%
this book out a long time
ago, when you launched it?

00:24:11.850 --> 00:24:13.870 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, there
were a considerable number

00:24:13.870 --> 00:24:17.890 align:middle line:84%
of physicians who developed an
enormous amount of intellectual

00:24:17.890 --> 00:24:19.210 align:middle line:90%
indigestion--

00:24:19.210 --> 00:24:21.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's funny.

00:24:21.060 --> 00:24:22.900 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: --over
this kind of thing.

00:24:22.900 --> 00:24:24.000 align:middle line:90%
But that was early on.

00:24:24.000 --> 00:24:27.710 align:middle line:84%
And I must say that
it is rare when

00:24:27.710 --> 00:24:30.000 align:middle line:84%
I talk to doctors
at medical schools

00:24:30.000 --> 00:24:33.860 align:middle line:84%
and hospitals for anyone
to object to any of this.

00:24:33.860 --> 00:24:35.950 align:middle line:84%
I had the opportunity to
talk to tens of thousands

00:24:35.950 --> 00:24:40.000 align:middle line:84%
of doctors in a year's
time about these issues.

00:24:40.000 --> 00:24:43.180 align:middle line:90%
Almost no one objects anymore.

00:24:43.180 --> 00:24:45.570 align:middle line:84%
And I think that the
reason is that it's

00:24:45.570 --> 00:24:51.840 align:middle line:84%
really tough to deny
the power of the data.

00:24:51.840 --> 00:24:55.350 align:middle line:84%
And most doctors may be
willing to say, well,

00:24:55.350 --> 00:24:57.190 align:middle line:84%
the data may be true,
but I just don't

00:24:57.190 --> 00:24:59.540 align:middle line:84%
feel good about doing
this with my patients.

00:24:59.540 --> 00:25:00.562 align:middle line:90%
That's their choice.

00:25:00.562 --> 00:25:02.020 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
should be honored.

00:25:02.020 --> 00:25:03.960 align:middle line:84%
But most physicians
have integrated this

00:25:03.960 --> 00:25:06.600 align:middle line:84%
into their practice
and the interaction

00:25:06.600 --> 00:25:08.917 align:middle line:90%
with patients to some degree.

00:25:08.917 --> 00:25:10.500 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I remember
you once telling me

00:25:10.500 --> 00:25:12.850 align:middle line:84%
that you used to speak at
the medical conventions,

00:25:12.850 --> 00:25:14.700 align:middle line:84%
and that when your
lecture would come up,

00:25:14.700 --> 00:25:16.800 align:middle line:90%
the room would be fairly empty.

00:25:16.800 --> 00:25:19.930 align:middle line:84%
And then you saw it
grow and grow and grow.

00:25:19.930 --> 00:25:22.530 align:middle line:84%
And this was the interest
being piqued by the doctors.

00:25:22.530 --> 00:25:23.550 align:middle line:90%
Do you remember that?

00:25:23.550 --> 00:25:24.230 align:middle line:90%
Do you remember telling me that?

00:25:24.230 --> 00:25:24.790 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: I do.

00:25:24.790 --> 00:25:26.998 align:middle line:84%
Actually, it's interesting
to talk about these issues

00:25:26.998 --> 00:25:32.040 align:middle line:84%
with groups of doctors, because
the same thing always happens.

00:25:32.040 --> 00:25:36.130 align:middle line:84%
After the talk is over
and people are filing out,

00:25:36.130 --> 00:25:39.770 align:middle line:84%
there are always a few doctors
who come up to the podium,

00:25:39.770 --> 00:25:42.770 align:middle line:84%
and they will say
things like, well, you

00:25:42.770 --> 00:25:45.200 align:middle line:84%
think what you talked
about is weird,

00:25:45.200 --> 00:25:48.060 align:middle line:84%
let me tell you what I've
seen with my patients.

00:25:48.060 --> 00:25:50.650 align:middle line:90%
And so the stories come forth.

00:25:50.650 --> 00:25:52.180 align:middle line:84%
And I collect those
and occasionally

00:25:52.180 --> 00:25:54.391 align:middle line:90%
use them in my own writing.

00:25:54.391 --> 00:25:56.140 align:middle line:84%
Can I give you one
that happened recently?

00:25:56.140 --> 00:25:57.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, definitely.

00:25:57.180 --> 00:26:04.130 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: It had to do with a
talk I gave about premonitions.

00:26:04.130 --> 00:26:08.210 align:middle line:84%
And I revealed to the
doctors my own experiences.

00:26:08.210 --> 00:26:12.190 align:middle line:84%
And in the Q&A session, a
female internist stood up

00:26:12.190 --> 00:26:15.410 align:middle line:84%
and she said, well,
I get numbers.

00:26:15.410 --> 00:26:17.630 align:middle line:90%
I get numbers in my dreams.

00:26:17.630 --> 00:26:22.210 align:middle line:84%
She said, I see the specific
values of my patients' lab

00:26:22.210 --> 00:26:24.568 align:middle line:84%
tests before I even
order the tests.

00:26:24.568 --> 00:26:25.526 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh my goodness.

00:26:25.526 --> 00:26:25.620 align:middle line:90%
Wow.

00:26:25.620 --> 00:26:27.220 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So this
is the sort of thing

00:26:27.220 --> 00:26:29.970 align:middle line:84%
that doctors can
come forward with,

00:26:29.970 --> 00:26:32.150 align:middle line:84%
and I think it's
quite interesting.

00:26:32.150 --> 00:26:35.960 align:middle line:84%
Because it shows this-- if
you give doctors a safe place

00:26:35.960 --> 00:26:39.870 align:middle line:84%
to talk about weird
experiences, whether prayer,

00:26:39.870 --> 00:26:43.640 align:middle line:84%
distant healing,
and so on, you may

00:26:43.640 --> 00:26:46.070 align:middle line:84%
be surprised what
they come up with.

00:26:46.070 --> 00:26:48.400 align:middle line:84%
I think most doctors
have a long laundry

00:26:48.400 --> 00:26:51.030 align:middle line:84%
list of these experiences
with their patients

00:26:51.030 --> 00:26:53.270 align:middle line:84%
that they're just reluctant
to talk about publicly.

00:26:53.270 --> 00:26:55.600 align:middle line:84%
But they will under
certain circumstances.

00:26:55.600 --> 00:26:58.100 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You told me about
another doctor friend of yours

00:26:58.100 --> 00:27:00.150 align:middle line:90%
who is an OB/GYN.

00:27:00.150 --> 00:27:00.940 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Yes.

00:27:00.940 --> 00:27:03.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And he
believes-- how does he

00:27:03.640 --> 00:27:05.020 align:middle line:90%
use that power of premonition?

00:27:05.020 --> 00:27:07.970 align:middle line:84%
Which is actually another
one of Dr. Dossey's books.

00:27:07.970 --> 00:27:14.390 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well he has a
strange sensation in his chest

00:27:14.390 --> 00:27:17.770 align:middle line:84%
every time one of his
patients is about to deliver.

00:27:17.770 --> 00:27:19.980 align:middle line:90%
And this never fails.

00:27:19.980 --> 00:27:22.630 align:middle line:84%
And he has a
premonition about when

00:27:22.630 --> 00:27:24.890 align:middle line:84%
the baby's coming
that's connected

00:27:24.890 --> 00:27:26.350 align:middle line:90%
with a bodily symptom.

00:27:26.350 --> 00:27:29.050 align:middle line:84%
Now this seems really bizarre,
but this is in the literature.

00:27:29.050 --> 00:27:31.600 align:middle line:90%
This does take place.

00:27:31.600 --> 00:27:36.170 align:middle line:84%
And it's an indicator
that premonitions

00:27:36.170 --> 00:27:39.250 align:middle line:84%
are valid if they're associated
with a bodily symptom.

00:27:39.250 --> 00:27:44.350 align:middle line:84%
This proves to be so reliable
that the nurses on the OB/GYN

00:27:44.350 --> 00:27:47.850 align:middle line:84%
floor of the hospital where he
works tell each other, well,

00:27:47.850 --> 00:27:50.800 align:middle line:84%
if you're uncertain when she's
going to deliver her baby, just

00:27:50.800 --> 00:27:54.265 align:middle line:84%
call Dr. So-and-So up and ask
him how his chest is feeling.

00:27:54.265 --> 00:27:55.640 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So it
actually has proven

00:27:55.640 --> 00:27:56.590 align:middle line:90%
to be right that many times.

00:27:56.590 --> 00:27:58.465 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So they use
this as a clinical sign

00:27:58.465 --> 00:28:00.200 align:middle line:84%
of when the woman's
going to deliver.

00:28:00.200 --> 00:28:01.866 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I mean, let's
go into that more.

00:28:01.866 --> 00:28:06.595 align:middle line:84%
So 59% of doctors pray for
their patients individually.

00:28:06.595 --> 00:28:07.360 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Mhm.

00:28:07.360 --> 00:28:08.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: 59%.

00:28:08.260 --> 00:28:10.410 align:middle line:84%
And this was a
survey that was done.

00:28:10.410 --> 00:28:14.920 align:middle line:84%
51% pray for
patients as a group.

00:28:14.920 --> 00:28:17.980 align:middle line:84%
So in a group setting, they
pay-- pray for their patients?

00:28:17.980 --> 00:28:20.277 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: They'll pray for
their patients collectively.

00:28:20.277 --> 00:28:20.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I see.

00:28:20.860 --> 00:28:23.270 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: They'll pray
for the best outcome

00:28:23.270 --> 00:28:27.476 align:middle line:84%
or for a specific thing
to happen as a group.

00:28:27.476 --> 00:28:28.600 align:middle line:90%
They don't single them out.

00:28:28.600 --> 00:28:33.470 align:middle line:84%
But they pray privately
for their patients

00:28:33.470 --> 00:28:34.700 align:middle line:90%
as a collective whole.

00:28:34.700 --> 00:28:37.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then 42%
encourage patients

00:28:37.580 --> 00:28:39.300 align:middle line:90%
to pray for themselves.

00:28:39.300 --> 00:28:43.180 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Yes, and they do it,
not just to give something--

00:28:43.180 --> 00:28:45.010 align:middle line:84%
give their patient
something to do,

00:28:45.010 --> 00:28:49.670 align:middle line:84%
but they do it because they
think prayer is likely to work.

00:28:49.670 --> 00:28:51.650 align:middle line:84%
Doctors are very
pragmatic people.

00:28:51.650 --> 00:28:53.490 align:middle line:90%
They use what works.

00:28:53.490 --> 00:28:56.080 align:middle line:84%
They'll generally throw the
kitchen sink at anything

00:28:56.080 --> 00:28:58.830 align:middle line:84%
if they think there's
a chance it might work.

00:28:58.830 --> 00:29:02.950 align:middle line:84%
So the reason over half of
doctors pray for their patients

00:29:02.950 --> 00:29:05.550 align:middle line:84%
or encourage them to pray for
themselves is because they

00:29:05.550 --> 00:29:07.610 align:middle line:84%
think there's good
data suggesting

00:29:07.610 --> 00:29:09.170 align:middle line:90%
that this can be effective.

00:29:09.170 --> 00:29:12.312 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, there's
zero side effects as well.

00:29:12.312 --> 00:29:13.770 align:middle line:84%
That's the beautiful
part about it.

00:29:13.770 --> 00:29:15.394 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I'm glad
you brought that up.

00:29:15.394 --> 00:29:17.322 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:29:17.322 --> 00:29:18.780 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: As opposed
to other things.

00:29:18.780 --> 00:29:21.200 align:middle line:84%
So there has, as
you would say, there

00:29:21.200 --> 00:29:26.720 align:middle line:84%
has been a re-spiritualization
of medicine in your experience.

00:29:26.720 --> 00:29:28.420 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: There's
no doubt about it.

00:29:28.420 --> 00:29:30.270 align:middle line:84%
I've already mentioned
that almost none

00:29:30.270 --> 00:29:32.100 align:middle line:84%
of the medical
schools 20 years ago

00:29:32.100 --> 00:29:33.690 align:middle line:90%
had anything to do with this.

00:29:33.690 --> 00:29:35.990 align:middle line:90%
Now the great majority do.

00:29:35.990 --> 00:29:40.250 align:middle line:84%
Doctors are openly acknowledging
that they make a place

00:29:40.250 --> 00:29:42.520 align:middle line:84%
in their life, in
their practice life,

00:29:42.520 --> 00:29:44.710 align:middle line:84%
for prayer and
healing intentions.

00:29:44.710 --> 00:29:46.700 align:middle line:90%
So there's no going back.

00:29:46.700 --> 00:29:48.530 align:middle line:84%
And the reason I
keep coming back to,

00:29:48.530 --> 00:29:50.880 align:middle line:90%
Lisa, is because of the data.

00:29:50.880 --> 00:29:53.737 align:middle line:84%
I mean, there's just no
getting around the facts.

00:29:53.737 --> 00:29:55.320 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, that
is some of the data

00:29:55.320 --> 00:29:56.778 align:middle line:84%
that I actually
want to talk about.

00:29:56.778 --> 00:29:59.719 align:middle line:84%
I want to get into this and
what some of the-- as we've

00:29:59.719 --> 00:30:01.760 align:middle line:84%
talked about it a lot,
and we've quoted it a lot,

00:30:01.760 --> 00:30:04.990 align:middle line:84%
but what are some of the
actual scientific studies?

00:30:04.990 --> 00:30:06.670 align:middle line:84%
We're actually going
to go through that

00:30:06.670 --> 00:30:07.740 align:middle line:90%
in just a little bit.

00:30:07.740 --> 00:30:10.604 align:middle line:84%
But I wanted to talk a
little more about as doctors

00:30:10.604 --> 00:30:12.520 align:middle line:84%
are watching you, and
as patients are watching

00:30:12.520 --> 00:30:14.580 align:middle line:84%
this right now, and
they're understanding

00:30:14.580 --> 00:30:18.730 align:middle line:84%
that there could be some more
permission for this to happen

00:30:18.730 --> 00:30:21.480 align:middle line:84%
in their lives, do
you see the practices

00:30:21.480 --> 00:30:23.760 align:middle line:84%
and do you see hospitals
responding to this?

00:30:23.760 --> 00:30:27.170 align:middle line:84%
Do you see hospitals
creating programs or systems

00:30:27.170 --> 00:30:31.190 align:middle line:90%
around prayer used in healing?

00:30:31.190 --> 00:30:35.160 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, there
are many hospital systems

00:30:35.160 --> 00:30:38.110 align:middle line:84%
across the country who
go out of their way

00:30:38.110 --> 00:30:40.770 align:middle line:84%
to integrate this on
an inpatient basis.

00:30:40.770 --> 00:30:43.040 align:middle line:84%
And they-- the reason
they-- and the way

00:30:43.040 --> 00:30:45.960 align:middle line:84%
they usually go about it is
through hospital chaplains

00:30:45.960 --> 00:30:47.310 align:middle line:90%
and pastoral counselors.

00:30:47.310 --> 00:30:48.200 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:30:48.200 --> 00:30:50.000 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Many
institutions are still

00:30:50.000 --> 00:30:56.680 align:middle line:84%
very wary of making this
something that doctors do.

00:30:56.680 --> 00:30:59.600 align:middle line:84%
But doctors don't
have to do this.

00:30:59.600 --> 00:31:00.987 align:middle line:90%
People can pray for themselves.

00:31:00.987 --> 00:31:01.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:31:01.570 --> 00:31:03.028 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: You can
encourage friends

00:31:03.028 --> 00:31:05.850 align:middle line:84%
and loved ones to pray for
you if you're a patient.

00:31:05.850 --> 00:31:08.340 align:middle line:84%
And one of the most
responsive groups

00:31:08.340 --> 00:31:11.450 align:middle line:84%
in the whole country to this
emerging body of information

00:31:11.450 --> 00:31:14.261 align:middle line:84%
has been hospital chaplains
and pastoral counselors.

00:31:14.261 --> 00:31:15.260 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, I'm sure.

00:31:15.260 --> 00:31:16.926 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I have the
opportunity to talk

00:31:16.926 --> 00:31:18.910 align:middle line:84%
to groups of these at
their national meetings.

00:31:18.910 --> 00:31:23.910 align:middle line:84%
And they seem extraordinarily
grateful that science

00:31:23.910 --> 00:31:29.760 align:middle line:84%
has given them some ammunition
in the form of control studies

00:31:29.760 --> 00:31:32.860 align:middle line:84%
that when people pray,
they're not fooling themselves

00:31:32.860 --> 00:31:34.550 align:middle line:90%
into thinking this works.

00:31:34.550 --> 00:31:38.002 align:middle line:84%
There's actual information in
the form of data confirming it.

00:31:38.002 --> 00:31:39.710 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So let's talk
about some of that.

00:31:39.710 --> 00:31:41.970 align:middle line:84%
Some of the studies--
and this is as recent

00:31:41.970 --> 00:31:49.700 align:middle line:84%
as 2010-- around major
randomized controlled clinical

00:31:49.700 --> 00:31:51.600 align:middle line:84%
trials of distant
healings and so forth.

00:31:51.600 --> 00:31:53.308 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell us a
little bit about those?

00:31:53.308 --> 00:31:55.230 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well,
my favorite study

00:31:55.230 --> 00:32:00.440 align:middle line:84%
is one that was done by a
famous researcher in the imagery

00:32:00.440 --> 00:32:03.930 align:middle line:84%
and visualization field,
Dr. Jean Achterberg.

00:32:03.930 --> 00:32:07.680 align:middle line:84%
She was recruited to
the Big Island of Hawaii

00:32:07.680 --> 00:32:12.390 align:middle line:84%
by a funder who had
built this hospital.

00:32:12.390 --> 00:32:15.650 align:middle line:84%
And this guy was interested,
fantastically interested,

00:32:15.650 --> 00:32:17.270 align:middle line:90%
in healing.

00:32:17.270 --> 00:32:21.660 align:middle line:84%
So she recruited
11 native healers

00:32:21.660 --> 00:32:25.000 align:middle line:84%
from the Hawaii
healer community.

00:32:25.000 --> 00:32:27.930 align:middle line:84%
And she invited him them to
go out and select a patient

00:32:27.930 --> 00:32:31.390 align:middle line:84%
to work with, that they felt
really empathic and loving

00:32:31.390 --> 00:32:33.920 align:middle line:90%
and very close and caring with.

00:32:33.920 --> 00:32:35.660 align:middle line:84%
And so she did one
of these fancy what

00:32:35.660 --> 00:32:41.100 align:middle line:84%
are called fMRI studies, the
Functional Magnetic Resonance

00:32:41.100 --> 00:32:42.760 align:middle line:90%
Imaging study of the brain.

00:32:42.760 --> 00:32:44.220 align:middle line:90%
Here's how it worked.

00:32:44.220 --> 00:32:46.220 align:middle line:84%
The patient's head
or brain was being

00:32:46.220 --> 00:32:51.070 align:middle line:84%
scanned at the time the healer
was sending prayer or healing

00:32:51.070 --> 00:32:53.110 align:middle line:84%
intentions, whatever
they called it.

00:32:53.110 --> 00:32:55.080 align:middle line:84%
And these healing
intention periods

00:32:55.080 --> 00:32:57.930 align:middle line:84%
were interspersed with periods
when they didn't do anything.

00:32:57.930 --> 00:33:02.350 align:middle line:84%
And only during the period when
the healer was doing healing,

00:33:02.350 --> 00:33:07.180 align:middle line:84%
the brain of the subject
lit up in the fMRI scanner,

00:33:07.180 --> 00:33:10.170 align:middle line:84%
indicating increased
metabolic activity

00:33:10.170 --> 00:33:13.790 align:middle line:84%
only when the healer
was doing her thing.

00:33:13.790 --> 00:33:16.900 align:middle line:84%
And this happened in
10 of the 11 subjects.

00:33:16.900 --> 00:33:19.240 align:middle line:84%
This is an astonishing
study, really,

00:33:19.240 --> 00:33:22.450 align:middle line:84%
because I think it just
demolishes the idea that prayer

00:33:22.450 --> 00:33:25.830 align:middle line:84%
is just positive thinking or
placebo effects and so on.

00:33:25.830 --> 00:33:28.330 align:middle line:84%
The odds against a
chance explanation

00:33:28.330 --> 00:33:31.680 align:middle line:84%
of this phenomenon in that
study was less than one chance

00:33:31.680 --> 00:33:32.780 align:middle line:90%
in 10,000.

00:33:32.780 --> 00:33:33.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow

00:33:33.480 --> 00:33:35.480 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So this is
the sort of precision

00:33:35.480 --> 00:33:38.590 align:middle line:84%
that's being brought to looking
at the effects of prayer

00:33:38.590 --> 00:33:39.840 align:middle line:90%
and healing.

00:33:39.840 --> 00:33:42.450 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I remember you told me
about at Duke University there

00:33:42.450 --> 00:33:45.490 align:middle line:84%
were a number of studies
were done on, well,

00:33:45.490 --> 00:33:48.660 align:middle line:84%
specifically on control groups
where patients were prayed for

00:33:48.660 --> 00:33:50.630 align:middle line:84%
and those that were
not prayed for.

00:33:50.630 --> 00:33:52.680 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell us about
some of those results?

00:33:52.680 --> 00:33:57.570 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, the study was
done by Dr. Mitchell Krucoff

00:33:57.570 --> 00:33:59.010 align:middle line:90%
and in his team.

00:33:59.010 --> 00:34:01.220 align:middle line:84%
And in their initial
study, they found

00:34:01.220 --> 00:34:06.470 align:middle line:84%
that there was a major
decrease in side effects,

00:34:06.470 --> 00:34:08.449 align:middle line:84%
such as bleeding and
cardiac arrhythmias,

00:34:08.449 --> 00:34:12.550 align:middle line:84%
in patients who were undergoing
cardiac bypass surgery.

00:34:12.550 --> 00:34:15.820 align:middle line:84%
I must say, however, that
studies to replicate that

00:34:15.820 --> 00:34:19.510 align:middle line:84%
particular study
often have not worked.

00:34:19.510 --> 00:34:24.690 align:middle line:84%
The most famous study has been
done at Harvard Medical School

00:34:24.690 --> 00:34:28.949 align:middle line:84%
in 1,800 patients undergoing
cardiac bypass surgery.

00:34:28.949 --> 00:34:31.420 align:middle line:84%
It was an extremely
confusing study.

00:34:31.420 --> 00:34:33.050 align:middle line:84%
And I think one
reason it did not work

00:34:33.050 --> 00:34:35.230 align:middle line:84%
is because it
tried to use prayer

00:34:35.230 --> 00:34:39.159 align:middle line:84%
in a way in which it is
never used anywhere on Earth.

00:34:39.159 --> 00:34:40.520 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How?

00:34:40.520 --> 00:34:43.739 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I don't want
to be too complex about this,

00:34:43.739 --> 00:34:47.260 align:middle line:84%
but very briefly, one third
of these 1,800 patients

00:34:47.260 --> 00:34:50.260 align:middle line:84%
were told that they
would be given prayer,

00:34:50.260 --> 00:34:51.920 align:middle line:90%
and they were given prayer.

00:34:51.920 --> 00:34:52.940 align:middle line:90%
They were prayed for.

00:34:52.940 --> 00:34:53.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:34:53.440 --> 00:34:57.100 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: A third were told
you might be prayed for

00:34:57.100 --> 00:34:58.790 align:middle line:90%
or you might not be.

00:34:58.790 --> 00:35:00.200 align:middle line:90%
And they were prayed for.

00:35:00.200 --> 00:35:03.470 align:middle line:84%
And a third were told, you
might get prayer, maybe not.

00:35:03.470 --> 00:35:05.360 align:middle line:90%
And they were not prayed for.

00:35:05.360 --> 00:35:07.610 align:middle line:84%
Now, you would think that
the group that would do best

00:35:07.610 --> 00:35:11.550 align:middle line:84%
if prayer works was this first
group who were guaranteed they

00:35:11.550 --> 00:35:13.980 align:middle line:84%
were going to get prayed for
and they were prayed for.

00:35:13.980 --> 00:35:16.630 align:middle line:84%
As it turned out, this
group did the worst of all.

00:35:16.630 --> 00:35:20.120 align:middle line:84%
They had the highest incidence
of side effects following

00:35:20.120 --> 00:35:22.890 align:middle line:90%
cardiac bypass surgery.

00:35:22.890 --> 00:35:23.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:35:23.640 --> 00:35:26.480 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: So what happened here?

00:35:26.480 --> 00:35:29.850 align:middle line:84%
My interpretation of
this is that it violated

00:35:29.850 --> 00:35:31.890 align:middle line:84%
what's called ecological
validity, which

00:35:31.890 --> 00:35:34.730 align:middle line:84%
means that it
tried to use prayer

00:35:34.730 --> 00:35:36.850 align:middle line:90%
unlike it's used in real life.

00:35:36.850 --> 00:35:38.930 align:middle line:90%
I'll give you an example.

00:35:38.930 --> 00:35:41.810 align:middle line:84%
If you went to your
mother's bedside tonight,

00:35:41.810 --> 00:35:45.870 align:middle line:84%
and she was scheduled to have
bypass surgery tomorrow, you

00:35:45.870 --> 00:35:48.465 align:middle line:84%
would not say,
mom, I know you're

00:35:48.465 --> 00:35:50.090 align:middle line:84%
going to have a big
operation tomorrow,

00:35:50.090 --> 00:35:53.200 align:middle line:84%
but I'm just not sure I'm
going to pray for you.

00:35:53.200 --> 00:35:54.070 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, no.

00:35:54.070 --> 00:35:55.740 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: You would not do this.

00:35:55.740 --> 00:35:55.930 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely not.

00:35:55.930 --> 00:35:56.920 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: It would be inhumane.

00:35:56.920 --> 00:35:57.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:35:57.590 --> 00:35:59.631 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: But this is what
was done, essentially,

00:35:59.631 --> 00:36:02.640 align:middle line:84%
in 2/3 of these patients
in the Harvard study.

00:36:02.640 --> 00:36:04.850 align:middle line:84%
So you have to ask
yourself, well, maybe that

00:36:04.850 --> 00:36:09.500 align:middle line:84%
stirred up some emotions that
are not healthy in people.

00:36:09.500 --> 00:36:13.056 align:middle line:84%
And maybe the people who
weren't sure they were going--

00:36:13.056 --> 00:36:14.430 align:middle line:84%
they were gonna
get prayer or not

00:36:14.430 --> 00:36:17.230 align:middle line:84%
would have recruited extra
prayer from outside, from loved

00:36:17.230 --> 00:36:18.360 align:middle line:90%
ones and friends.

00:36:18.360 --> 00:36:21.440 align:middle line:84%
Or maybe they would double
down on their own self prayer.

00:36:21.440 --> 00:36:25.940 align:middle line:84%
So this study was absolutely
confused, in my opinion.

00:36:25.940 --> 00:36:28.600 align:middle line:84%
But it's had a terrible
effect, because a lot of people

00:36:28.600 --> 00:36:32.270 align:middle line:84%
say, well, Harvard
disproved that prayer works.

00:36:32.270 --> 00:36:35.640 align:middle line:84%
And I think this is a complete
misinterpretation of the facts.

00:36:35.640 --> 00:36:37.310 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, indeed
there are studies

00:36:37.310 --> 00:36:38.880 align:middle line:84%
that of course
show the opposite.

00:36:38.880 --> 00:36:40.185 align:middle line:90%
And there's many of them.

00:36:40.185 --> 00:36:41.810 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, there
are many of them.

00:36:41.810 --> 00:36:46.980 align:middle line:84%
By my count, there are 22
major studies in humans.

00:36:46.980 --> 00:36:49.670 align:middle line:84%
At least half of these show
statistically significant

00:36:49.670 --> 00:36:50.840 align:middle line:90%
results.

00:36:50.840 --> 00:36:53.020 align:middle line:84%
If you enlarge that to look
at the effects of prayer

00:36:53.020 --> 00:36:56.820 align:middle line:84%
and healing intentions on
animals and plants and so,

00:36:56.820 --> 00:37:00.230 align:middle line:84%
there are over 200 of these
studies, most of which

00:37:00.230 --> 00:37:00.870 align:middle line:90%
are positive.

00:37:00.870 --> 00:37:02.786 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I want to actually
ask you about that.

00:37:02.786 --> 00:37:04.744 align:middle line:84%
The plants and the
animals and so forth.

00:37:04.744 --> 00:37:06.160 align:middle line:84%
There were studies
that I remember

00:37:06.160 --> 00:37:09.960 align:middle line:84%
being done on funguses,
on plant growth.

00:37:09.960 --> 00:37:12.672 align:middle line:84%
These are things that people
can do at home, which I love.

00:37:12.672 --> 00:37:14.130 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: You can
try this at home.

00:37:14.130 --> 00:37:15.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You can
try this at home.

00:37:15.050 --> 00:37:16.280 align:middle line:84%
I recommended you
try this at home.

00:37:16.280 --> 00:37:17.820 align:middle line:84%
Tell us a little
bit about those.

00:37:17.820 --> 00:37:19.278 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well as
a matter of fact,

00:37:19.278 --> 00:37:23.966 align:middle line:84%
these are my favorite studies,
which may sound surprising.

00:37:23.966 --> 00:37:25.590 align:middle line:84%
Why not do all these
studies on people?

00:37:25.590 --> 00:37:27.070 align:middle line:84%
That's what we're
concerned with.

00:37:27.070 --> 00:37:30.960 align:middle line:84%
Well, the reason is that if you
do a study on animals-- rats,

00:37:30.960 --> 00:37:34.920 align:middle line:84%
mice, plants, growth rates
of bacteria in test tubes

00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:37.800 align:middle line:84%
and that sort of thing--
and the study is positive,

00:37:37.800 --> 00:37:41.660 align:middle line:84%
you can't explain
it away by saying

00:37:41.660 --> 00:37:43.250 align:middle line:84%
it was just the
placebo response.

00:37:43.250 --> 00:37:43.833 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:37:43.833 --> 00:37:46.780 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Or it just happened
because of positive thinking.

00:37:46.780 --> 00:37:49.337 align:middle line:84%
As far as we know, bacteria
don't think positively.

00:37:49.337 --> 00:37:49.920 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:37:49.920 --> 00:37:50.220 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Right?

00:37:50.220 --> 00:37:50.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:37:50.640 --> 00:37:52.306 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So if you
get a positive study

00:37:52.306 --> 00:37:57.090 align:middle line:84%
in the creatures, you've
really got some big stuff here.

00:37:57.090 --> 00:37:58.852 align:middle line:84%
Because you can't
explain it away--

00:37:58.852 --> 00:38:00.060 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Something more valid.

00:38:00.060 --> 00:38:02.120 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: --by calling
it the placebo response.

00:38:02.120 --> 00:38:02.860 align:middle line:90%
It doesn't work.

00:38:02.860 --> 00:38:03.860 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what
were the studies?

00:38:03.860 --> 00:38:05.693 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell us a little
bit about-- I mean,

00:38:05.693 --> 00:38:07.180 align:middle line:90%
just a couple of them,.

00:38:07.180 --> 00:38:09.880 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, there was one
study looking at the healing

00:38:09.880 --> 00:38:15.500 align:middle line:84%
rates of surgical
wounds in mice.

00:38:15.500 --> 00:38:17.280 align:middle line:90%
And I don't justify--

00:38:17.280 --> 00:38:18.530 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Animals testing, yeah.

00:38:18.530 --> 00:38:19.880 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: --animal testing.

00:38:19.880 --> 00:38:23.220 align:middle line:84%
But this is just part of
the history of this field.

00:38:23.220 --> 00:38:26.719 align:middle line:84%
And those animals that were
prayed for healed up faster.

00:38:26.719 --> 00:38:29.010 align:middle line:84%
And you can measure the
healing rate of surgical wounds

00:38:29.010 --> 00:38:30.500 align:middle line:90%
very precisely.

00:38:30.500 --> 00:38:32.080 align:middle line:84%
And so there was
a treatment group

00:38:32.080 --> 00:38:34.230 align:middle line:84%
that was not prayed
for increased healing

00:38:34.230 --> 00:38:35.910 align:middle line:90%
and versus the one that was.

00:38:35.910 --> 00:38:39.560 align:middle line:84%
And as in most of these
studies, the group that got

00:38:39.560 --> 00:38:42.610 align:middle line:84%
prayed for healed up
quicker than the group that

00:38:42.610 --> 00:38:45.940 align:middle line:90%
did not receive healing prayer.

00:38:45.940 --> 00:38:48.000 align:middle line:90%
The bacteria are interesting.

00:38:48.000 --> 00:38:53.750 align:middle line:84%
So it shows that there's a
huge variety of living things,

00:38:53.750 --> 00:38:56.670 align:middle line:84%
living organisms, that
respond to prayer.

00:38:56.670 --> 00:38:58.250 align:middle line:84%
When you pray for
an increased growth

00:38:58.250 --> 00:39:01.386 align:middle line:84%
rate in the bacteria in these
test tubes and not these,

00:39:01.386 --> 00:39:03.950 align:middle line:84%
these grow faster,
statistically speaking,

00:39:03.950 --> 00:39:05.820 align:middle line:90%
in the majority of studies.

00:39:05.820 --> 00:39:07.270 align:middle line:90%
And so I love this.

00:39:07.270 --> 00:39:09.460 align:middle line:84%
Because it says this
is a general principle

00:39:09.460 --> 00:39:13.340 align:middle line:84%
throughout nature of response
to healing intentions in prayer.

00:39:13.340 --> 00:39:14.340 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That is amazing.

00:39:14.340 --> 00:39:15.670 align:middle line:90%
No, that's really interesting.

00:39:15.670 --> 00:39:18.280 align:middle line:84%
Have you ever tried this at
home with yourself, with plants,

00:39:18.280 --> 00:39:19.135 align:middle line:90%
and I mean you probably have a--

00:39:19.135 --> 00:39:20.630 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Oh, I pray for
my plants all the time.

00:39:20.630 --> 00:39:22.387 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --a
greenhouse, don't you?

00:39:22.387 --> 00:39:22.886 align:middle line:90%
You must.

00:39:22.886 --> 00:39:28.530 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Yeah, I'm an obsessive
pray-er for my-- all the living

00:39:28.530 --> 00:39:29.580 align:middle line:90%
things around my house.

00:39:29.580 --> 00:39:31.316 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I can imagine.

00:39:31.316 --> 00:39:33.690 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Actually, I've had
