you're in a different location?

00:43:20.500 --> 00:43:22.350 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, most
of these studies

00:43:22.350 --> 00:43:24.270 align:middle line:84%
actually have
involved healers who

00:43:24.270 --> 00:43:26.490 align:middle line:90%
were not on site at the bedside.

00:43:26.490 --> 00:43:27.300 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:43:27.300 --> 00:43:29.240 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And so
these, by and large,

00:43:29.240 --> 00:43:32.590 align:middle line:90%
are studies in remote healing.

00:43:32.590 --> 00:43:35.510 align:middle line:84%
You know, the reason that
physicians and researchers

00:43:35.510 --> 00:43:39.360 align:middle line:84%
do the remote thing is that if
you're standing at the bedside,

00:43:39.360 --> 00:43:44.340 align:middle line:84%
the patient knows you're there,
you know, and so this stirs up

00:43:44.340 --> 00:43:46.000 align:middle line:90%
all sorts of positive thinking.

00:43:46.000 --> 00:43:48.290 align:middle line:84%
And the skeptics
can say, well, it

00:43:48.290 --> 00:43:50.020 align:middle line:84%
wasn't the prayer
that did anything.

00:43:50.020 --> 00:43:52.430 align:middle line:84%
The person knew you
were praying for them,

00:43:52.430 --> 00:43:54.110 align:middle line:84%
and they just wanted
to help it along,

00:43:54.110 --> 00:43:58.210 align:middle line:84%
and so nothing is happening
as far as the prayer.

00:43:58.210 --> 00:44:02.475 align:middle line:84%
But if you have a praying
individual off 50,

00:44:02.475 --> 00:44:05.950 align:middle line:84%
100 miles away,
and the stuff works

00:44:05.950 --> 00:44:08.710 align:middle line:84%
when the individual doesn't
even know it's happening,

00:44:08.710 --> 00:44:10.630 align:middle line:84%
then you've really
got something there.

00:44:10.630 --> 00:44:11.546 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's so funny.

00:44:11.546 --> 00:44:13.610 align:middle line:84%
There is such a need
for the skeptics.

00:44:13.610 --> 00:44:15.290 align:middle line:84%
There really is a
need for the skeptics.

00:44:15.290 --> 00:44:18.550 align:middle line:84%
I look at this as something
to scientifically quantify

00:44:18.550 --> 00:44:21.140 align:middle line:84%
something that I instinctively
already know and have

00:44:21.140 --> 00:44:22.600 align:middle line:90%
used and tried all of my life.

00:44:22.600 --> 00:44:26.970 align:middle line:84%
And anyone who's ever prayed
to God knows that it works.

00:44:26.970 --> 00:44:27.850 align:middle line:90%
But this is great.

00:44:27.850 --> 00:44:30.110 align:middle line:84%
No, it's really great to
validate this within science.

00:44:30.110 --> 00:44:32.109 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I so
appreciate what you've done.

00:44:32.109 --> 00:44:34.732 align:middle line:84%
But you have used this all
your life, haven't you?

00:44:34.732 --> 00:44:35.690 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I have.

00:44:35.690 --> 00:44:39.130 align:middle line:84%
See, I grew up in an
intensely religious community

00:44:39.130 --> 00:44:41.340 align:middle line:90%
in central Texas.

00:44:41.340 --> 00:44:43.750 align:middle line:90%
It wasn't just the Bible Belt.

00:44:43.750 --> 00:44:46.740 align:middle line:84%
We called it the Buckle
of the Bible Belt.

00:44:46.740 --> 00:44:50.330 align:middle line:84%
Everybody just accepted that
this was the way it was.

00:44:50.330 --> 00:44:52.740 align:middle line:90%
But that didn't stick on me.

00:44:52.740 --> 00:44:55.220 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I went away to
university and medical school,

00:44:55.220 --> 00:44:58.990 align:middle line:84%
and I became a self-respecting
agnostic atheist

00:44:58.990 --> 00:45:03.530 align:middle line:84%
and bought into the idea
of complete materialistic

00:45:03.530 --> 00:45:04.960 align:middle line:90%
approaches to healing.

00:45:04.960 --> 00:45:07.100 align:middle line:84%
And I was told that no
good doctor believed

00:45:07.100 --> 00:45:10.910 align:middle line:84%
in any of this California
woo-woo healing intention

00:45:10.910 --> 00:45:11.600 align:middle line:90%
stuff.

00:45:11.600 --> 00:45:13.550 align:middle line:84%
And so I bought that
for several years

00:45:13.550 --> 00:45:17.830 align:middle line:84%
until I began to regrow
my own spiritual roots

00:45:17.830 --> 00:45:24.160 align:middle line:84%
and actually just had a
violent encounter in 1988 when

00:45:24.160 --> 00:45:27.280 align:middle line:84%
the first randomized
controlled study of prayer that

00:45:27.280 --> 00:45:30.560 align:middle line:84%
was really high
quality was published.

00:45:30.560 --> 00:45:32.440 align:middle line:90%
And it really got my attention.

00:45:32.440 --> 00:45:34.980 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't a comfortable
experience for me, either.

00:45:34.980 --> 00:45:36.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It doesn't
seem like it would.

00:45:36.900 --> 00:45:37.960 align:middle line:90%
You were angry about it?

00:45:37.960 --> 00:45:41.670 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I thought,
who in their right mind

00:45:41.670 --> 00:45:43.870 align:middle line:84%
would study prayer
like you would

00:45:43.870 --> 00:45:46.720 align:middle line:84%
a new medication,
control group that

00:45:46.720 --> 00:45:49.810 align:middle line:84%
didn't get the therapy and
a treatment group that did?

00:45:49.810 --> 00:45:52.920 align:middle line:84%
And I was really
troubled by that.

00:45:52.920 --> 00:45:54.146 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Why?

00:45:54.146 --> 00:45:55.520 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well,
because I thought

00:45:55.520 --> 00:45:59.510 align:middle line:84%
I'd dealt with that in my
spiritual religious past

00:45:59.510 --> 00:46:00.870 align:middle line:90%
and had put that to bed.

00:46:00.870 --> 00:46:05.040 align:middle line:84%
And here is this Dr. Randolph
Byrd at San Francisco General

00:46:05.040 --> 00:46:10.210 align:middle line:84%
Hospital who has come forward
to do this audacious study

00:46:10.210 --> 00:46:13.550 align:middle line:84%
with these preposterous findings
that this stuff appeared

00:46:13.550 --> 00:46:14.650 align:middle line:90%
to work.

00:46:14.650 --> 00:46:18.800 align:middle line:84%
And I was uncomfortable
with it because I

00:46:18.800 --> 00:46:23.570 align:middle line:84%
didn't have any
inclination to use this.

00:46:23.570 --> 00:46:25.540 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't have
prayed for my patients

00:46:25.540 --> 00:46:27.437 align:middle line:84%
on a bet at that
time in my life.

00:46:27.437 --> 00:46:28.270 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:46:28.270 --> 00:46:30.353 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: But you know,
you confront these things,

00:46:30.353 --> 00:46:33.010 align:middle line:84%
and you have to ask, well, if
the stuff works and I'm not

00:46:33.010 --> 00:46:36.270 align:middle line:84%
doing it, do I have
an ethical issue?

00:46:36.270 --> 00:46:39.775 align:middle line:84%
Should I be using something
that has been shown to work?

00:46:39.775 --> 00:46:41.650 align:middle line:84%
It would be like saying,
well, I just kind of

00:46:41.650 --> 00:46:44.142 align:middle line:84%
have an idea that I don't
want to use penicillin.

00:46:44.142 --> 00:46:46.100 align:middle line:84%
And there are all these
other studies out there

00:46:46.100 --> 00:46:50.140 align:middle line:84%
that show that you better
use it in certain infections.

00:46:50.140 --> 00:46:53.160 align:middle line:84%
And this was sort of my-- like
my confrontation with prayer.

00:46:53.160 --> 00:46:54.860 align:middle line:90%
Should I be using it?

00:46:54.860 --> 00:46:58.000 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so you came full
circle with this from the Bible

00:46:58.000 --> 00:47:01.764 align:middle line:84%
Belt, the buckle,
to the agnostic--

00:47:01.764 --> 00:47:02.430 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Right.

00:47:02.430 --> 00:47:06.240 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: --to now being the
advocate of bringing prayer

00:47:06.240 --> 00:47:09.730 align:middle line:84%
back in and its effectiveness
from a scientific founding

00:47:09.730 --> 00:47:12.360 align:middle line:84%
level into the
medical community.

00:47:12.360 --> 00:47:12.870 align:middle line:90%
Awesome.

00:47:12.870 --> 00:47:14.400 align:middle line:90%
That's why you're here.

00:47:14.400 --> 00:47:16.110 align:middle line:84%
That's why you have
these amazing--

00:47:16.110 --> 00:47:17.930 align:middle line:90%
you've made such an impact.

00:47:17.930 --> 00:47:18.700 align:middle line:90%
That's beautiful.

00:47:18.700 --> 00:47:20.658 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, we don't
always know the twists

00:47:20.658 --> 00:47:22.180 align:middle line:90%
and turns in our careers, do we?

00:47:22.180 --> 00:47:22.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: But look back.

00:47:22.820 --> 00:47:23.320 align:middle line:90%
It's great.

00:47:23.320 --> 00:47:24.180 align:middle line:90%
It's great.

00:47:24.180 --> 00:47:26.850 align:middle line:84%
So, about the
remote viewing, how

00:47:26.850 --> 00:47:31.540 align:middle line:84%
do they quantify that
that is absolutely valid?

00:47:31.540 --> 00:47:34.930 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I think
people have an ability

00:47:34.930 --> 00:47:38.910 align:middle line:84%
to acquire information
from the world out there.

00:47:38.910 --> 00:47:42.160 align:middle line:84%
This is called remote
viewing in some circles.

00:47:42.160 --> 00:47:46.050 align:middle line:84%
I think that this gets to be
very interesting in medicine

00:47:46.050 --> 00:47:49.270 align:middle line:84%
because people can know
things at a distance

00:47:49.270 --> 00:47:52.780 align:middle line:90%
without any sensory assistance.

00:47:52.780 --> 00:47:55.290 align:middle line:84%
And here's where it actually
begins to get interesting.

00:47:55.290 --> 00:47:57.720 align:middle line:84%
People can know things
about their own body

00:47:57.720 --> 00:48:02.310 align:middle line:84%
without any sort of mechanical
intervention at all.

00:48:02.310 --> 00:48:04.595 align:middle line:84%
Let me give you an example
about how this operates.

00:48:04.595 --> 00:48:07.430 align:middle line:90%


00:48:07.430 --> 00:48:10.040 align:middle line:84%
A friend of mine had a
patient who came to him.

00:48:10.040 --> 00:48:12.180 align:middle line:90%
He was a family physician.

00:48:12.180 --> 00:48:15.960 align:middle line:84%
And this woman said,
I have breast cancer,

00:48:15.960 --> 00:48:17.270 align:middle line:90%
and it's right here.

00:48:17.270 --> 00:48:20.090 align:middle line:84%
And she took an index finger
and pointed to a specific point

00:48:20.090 --> 00:48:23.980 align:middle line:84%
in her breast and said,
this is where my cancer is.

00:48:23.980 --> 00:48:25.890 align:middle line:90%
And so he did an exam.

00:48:25.890 --> 00:48:27.600 align:middle line:90%
It was completely normal.

00:48:27.600 --> 00:48:31.560 align:middle line:84%
They even did a mammogram,
and it was totally normal.

00:48:31.560 --> 00:48:33.600 align:middle line:90%
And she said, I don't care.

00:48:33.600 --> 00:48:34.780 align:middle line:90%
I know it's here.

00:48:34.780 --> 00:48:38.230 align:middle line:84%
And I want-- I demand
a breast biopsy.

00:48:38.230 --> 00:48:38.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:48:38.730 --> 00:48:40.688 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So she wouldn't
let him off the hook.

00:48:40.688 --> 00:48:43.270 align:middle line:84%
And so he phoned
up a friend of his

00:48:43.270 --> 00:48:45.150 align:middle line:90%
who was a cancer breast surgeon.

00:48:45.150 --> 00:48:49.830 align:middle line:84%
And he said, look, please
biopsy this woman's breast.

00:48:49.830 --> 00:48:52.200 align:middle line:84%
And he said, there's
nothing to biopsy.

00:48:52.200 --> 00:48:53.305 align:middle line:90%
Where would I biopsy?

00:48:53.305 --> 00:48:54.180 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, right.

00:48:54.180 --> 00:48:56.388 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And so the doctor
said, well, I don't know.

00:48:56.388 --> 00:48:59.910 align:middle line:90%
Just biopsy where she points.

00:48:59.910 --> 00:49:04.070 align:middle line:84%
So it sounds like a comedy,
but the doctor did the biopsy,

00:49:04.070 --> 00:49:07.250 align:middle line:84%
and he, a couple
days later, phoned

00:49:07.250 --> 00:49:11.900 align:middle line:84%
the referring first doctor,
and he said, it's cancer.

00:49:11.900 --> 00:49:15.370 align:middle line:84%
This is the most microscopic
cancer I have seen in years.

00:49:15.370 --> 00:49:16.760 align:middle line:90%
How did you find it?

00:49:16.760 --> 00:49:18.501 align:middle line:84%
It wouldn't have shown
up on a mammogram

00:49:18.501 --> 00:49:19.500 align:middle line:90%
or you couldn't feel it.

00:49:19.500 --> 00:49:21.190 align:middle line:90%
How did you know?

00:49:21.190 --> 00:49:24.710 align:middle line:84%
And this doctor, to his credit,
said, well, I didn't find it.

00:49:24.710 --> 00:49:26.260 align:middle line:90%
She did.

00:49:26.260 --> 00:49:28.662 align:middle line:90%
And she saw it in a dream.

00:49:28.662 --> 00:49:29.620 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh my goodness.

00:49:29.620 --> 00:49:33.240 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So this is
where consciousness

00:49:33.240 --> 00:49:37.820 align:middle line:84%
comes to be really important,
even in life and death

00:49:37.820 --> 00:49:42.080 align:middle line:84%
issues in medicine,
not just intentionality

00:49:42.080 --> 00:49:45.260 align:middle line:84%
and distant healing, not
just in remote viewing,

00:49:45.260 --> 00:49:48.130 align:middle line:84%
but the ability of
ourselves to use our minds

00:49:48.130 --> 00:49:51.770 align:middle line:84%
in a way that has
been denied possible

00:49:51.770 --> 00:49:53.687 align:middle line:84%
in the history of Western
scientific medicine.

00:49:53.687 --> 00:49:55.728 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Right, but if
somebody came in that says,

00:49:55.728 --> 00:49:58.125 align:middle line:84%
I had a dream, they would
think that person's crazy,

00:49:58.125 --> 00:50:00.540 align:middle line:84%
that they're a hypochondriac,
that they're intentionally

00:50:00.540 --> 00:50:02.900 align:middle line:84%
willing themselves to get
cancer to avoid an issue.

00:50:02.900 --> 00:50:03.858 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's right.

00:50:03.858 --> 00:50:06.140 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I mean,
you have dived deep

00:50:06.140 --> 00:50:08.460 align:middle line:84%
into this concept
of premonitions.

00:50:08.460 --> 00:50:11.360 align:middle line:84%
You wrote an entire
book about this,

00:50:11.360 --> 00:50:15.430 align:middle line:84%
about how people use the power
premonitions to diagnose,

00:50:15.430 --> 00:50:19.460 align:middle line:84%
to heal, to circumvent
events that have happened.

00:50:19.460 --> 00:50:21.280 align:middle line:84%
It's a very strong body
of work that you've

00:50:21.280 --> 00:50:24.580 align:middle line:84%
once again
scientifically qualified.

00:50:24.580 --> 00:50:27.600 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I didn't do it
willingly, Lisa, I must say.

00:50:27.600 --> 00:50:30.900 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I got into this
area kicking and screaming.

00:50:30.900 --> 00:50:32.290 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Again?

00:50:32.290 --> 00:50:34.080 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Again.

00:50:34.080 --> 00:50:36.460 align:middle line:90%
Yes, I did not go willingly.

00:50:36.460 --> 00:50:40.920 align:middle line:84%
But actually, like with
the prayer encounters,

00:50:40.920 --> 00:50:43.390 align:middle line:84%
I had some encounters
with premonitions

00:50:43.390 --> 00:50:45.580 align:middle line:90%
that I could not back away from.

00:50:45.580 --> 00:50:49.190 align:middle line:84%
The very first year I
was in medical practice

00:50:49.190 --> 00:50:52.880 align:middle line:84%
in internal medicine, I had a
series of dream premonitions

00:50:52.880 --> 00:50:54.450 align:middle line:90%
which absolutely shook me up.

00:50:54.450 --> 00:50:59.550 align:middle line:84%
And I knew the world was not
supposed to work like this.

00:50:59.550 --> 00:51:02.315 align:middle line:84%
And it took me a long time
to come to terms with that.

00:51:02.315 --> 00:51:04.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What were those?

00:51:04.020 --> 00:51:08.250 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I dreamt that
the three-year-old son of one

00:51:08.250 --> 00:51:14.510 align:middle line:84%
of my cardiology colleagues
was on an examining table.

00:51:14.510 --> 00:51:17.060 align:middle line:84%
And this was a
really weird dream.

00:51:17.060 --> 00:51:18.870 align:middle line:90%
I hardly knew this child.

00:51:18.870 --> 00:51:21.720 align:middle line:84%
And there was some
technician trying

00:51:21.720 --> 00:51:23.760 align:middle line:90%
to do a test on his head.

00:51:23.760 --> 00:51:27.580 align:middle line:84%
And the mother was
standing at the bedside,

00:51:27.580 --> 00:51:30.960 align:middle line:84%
and this kid went crazy,
fighting the technician,

00:51:30.960 --> 00:51:32.090 align:middle line:90%
screaming, crying.

00:51:32.090 --> 00:51:36.742 align:middle line:84%
And finally the technician just
says, I quit, and walks away.

00:51:36.742 --> 00:51:37.700 align:middle line:90%
And that was the dream.

00:51:37.700 --> 00:51:41.150 align:middle line:84%
And interestingly, this
was-- I swear, at the time,

00:51:41.150 --> 00:51:43.130 align:middle line:84%
this seemed like the most
vivid dream I've ever

00:51:43.130 --> 00:51:46.410 align:middle line:84%
had in my life, none of
which made any sense.

00:51:46.410 --> 00:51:48.990 align:middle line:84%
So I get up the next morning,
I go make hospital rounds.

00:51:48.990 --> 00:51:51.480 align:middle line:84%
And I'm sitting with the
father, the cardiologist,

00:51:51.480 --> 00:51:54.970 align:middle line:84%
of this young kid at
lunch when the wife walks

00:51:54.970 --> 00:51:58.680 align:middle line:84%
in holding this baby, this
child, and his hair is wet

00:51:58.680 --> 00:52:00.170 align:middle line:90%
and he's crying.

00:52:00.170 --> 00:52:04.380 align:middle line:84%
And she describes to
her husband my dream.

00:52:04.380 --> 00:52:06.630 align:middle line:84%
They had just come
from the EEG laboratory

00:52:06.630 --> 00:52:09.270 align:middle line:84%
where they tried to
do a brainwave test.

00:52:09.270 --> 00:52:12.900 align:middle line:90%
The child just went berserk.

00:52:12.900 --> 00:52:14.860 align:middle line:84%
The mother could
not calm the child.

00:52:14.860 --> 00:52:16.760 align:middle line:84%
Finally the technician
just gave up.

00:52:16.760 --> 00:52:20.350 align:middle line:84%
So she describes what I
dreamed the night before.

00:52:20.350 --> 00:52:22.770 align:middle line:84%
And I just didn't know
what to do with this.

00:52:22.770 --> 00:52:26.120 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I was sort of an
existential mini crisis.

00:52:26.120 --> 00:52:27.100 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Did you say?

00:52:27.100 --> 00:52:29.790 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, what I did--
she left with the little boy.

00:52:29.790 --> 00:52:33.520 align:middle line:84%
And I discussed this
with the father.

00:52:33.520 --> 00:52:36.970 align:middle line:84%
And I said, could I
have known about what

00:52:36.970 --> 00:52:38.470 align:middle line:84%
events were going
to play out today?

00:52:38.470 --> 00:52:41.110 align:middle line:90%
He said, what?

00:52:41.110 --> 00:52:42.620 align:middle line:90%
Of course not.

00:52:42.620 --> 00:52:49.940 align:middle line:84%
And so he-- I told him my dream,
and he became very anxious,

00:52:49.940 --> 00:52:53.840 align:middle line:84%
agitated, refused to
talk about it ever.

00:52:53.840 --> 00:52:57.470 align:middle line:84%
So he was absolutely
threatened that this experience

00:52:57.470 --> 00:52:58.160 align:middle line:90%
could occur.

00:52:58.160 --> 00:52:59.560 align:middle line:90%
I was uncomfortable, too.

00:52:59.560 --> 00:53:02.800 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Right, being two
physicians talking about it.

00:53:02.800 --> 00:53:05.700 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Right, so we knew
the world couldn't do this.

00:53:05.700 --> 00:53:07.760 align:middle line:90%
Things don't behave like this.

00:53:07.760 --> 00:53:10.140 align:middle line:84%
So I mentioned that
I'm a great denier.

00:53:10.140 --> 00:53:12.100 align:middle line:90%
So I tried to deny this one.

00:53:12.100 --> 00:53:14.730 align:middle line:84%
Actually, that didn't
work very well.

00:53:14.730 --> 00:53:18.080 align:middle line:84%
Because patients began
to describe to me

00:53:18.080 --> 00:53:20.250 align:middle line:90%
their own premonitions.

00:53:20.250 --> 00:53:21.230 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Unsolicited.

00:53:21.230 --> 00:53:22.600 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Unsolicited.

00:53:22.600 --> 00:53:25.085 align:middle line:84%
And then nurses
began to get wind

00:53:25.085 --> 00:53:27.570 align:middle line:84%
that Dossey's interested
in this stuff.

00:53:27.570 --> 00:53:32.130 align:middle line:84%
So they began to share
their experiences with me.

00:53:32.130 --> 00:53:34.984 align:middle line:84%
And so one thing led
to another, and--

00:53:34.984 --> 00:53:36.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that's how
you got into that book.

00:53:36.900 --> 00:53:38.210 align:middle line:90%
It's all combined, though.

00:53:38.210 --> 00:53:40.210 align:middle line:84%
I mean, basically everything
that you talk about

00:53:40.210 --> 00:53:42.650 align:middle line:90%
is about human consciousness.

00:53:42.650 --> 00:53:44.690 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: It's about how
consciousness manifests

00:53:44.690 --> 00:53:47.040 align:middle line:84%
in the world in
these strange ways

00:53:47.040 --> 00:53:49.590 align:middle line:84%
that we've been
really nervous about.

00:53:49.590 --> 00:53:54.060 align:middle line:84%
We haven't wanted to talk
about these things publicly.

00:53:54.060 --> 00:53:55.730 align:middle line:90%
But there's no going back.

00:53:55.730 --> 00:53:57.780 align:middle line:84%
You can't put this
genie back in the bottle

00:53:57.780 --> 00:54:01.120 align:middle line:84%
for the overwhelming reason
of the scientific studies.

00:54:01.120 --> 00:54:04.850 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So now we come to
this time and day in history

00:54:04.850 --> 00:54:08.310 align:middle line:84%
where consciousness
is actually discovered

00:54:08.310 --> 00:54:10.210 align:middle line:90%
to be valid scientifically.

00:54:10.210 --> 00:54:14.150 align:middle line:84%
There's a whole study about
this, about how consciousness

00:54:14.150 --> 00:54:16.402 align:middle line:84%
is valid in the
scientific community.

00:54:16.402 --> 00:54:18.610 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, actually
there are some enterprising,

00:54:18.610 --> 00:54:22.900 align:middle line:84%
courageous academicians
in many fields,

00:54:22.900 --> 00:54:26.270 align:middle line:84%
including mathematics and
cognitive science and physics,

00:54:26.270 --> 00:54:28.500 align:middle line:84%
who are standing
up for what they're

00:54:28.500 --> 00:54:31.460 align:middle line:84%
calling the fundamental
nature of consciousness.

00:54:31.460 --> 00:54:33.330 align:middle line:90%
I mean, this is a new ball game.

00:54:33.330 --> 00:54:37.150 align:middle line:84%
Because 20 and 30
and 40 years ago,

00:54:37.150 --> 00:54:40.810 align:middle line:84%
indeed during the 20th
century, the going idea

00:54:40.810 --> 00:54:45.110 align:middle line:84%
is that the brain makes
consciousness in ways nobody

00:54:45.110 --> 00:54:48.690 align:middle line:84%
understands, but consciousness
is just-- it just

00:54:48.690 --> 00:54:52.350 align:middle line:84%
emanates from the brain
in some strange way.

00:54:52.350 --> 00:54:54.830 align:middle line:84%
Sort of like the
liver makes bile.

00:54:54.830 --> 00:54:58.100 align:middle line:84%
The brain somehow
makes consciousness.

00:54:58.100 --> 00:55:00.014 align:middle line:90%
This has never been proved.

00:55:00.014 --> 00:55:01.430 align:middle line:84%
It's never been
directly observed.

00:55:01.430 --> 00:55:02.430 align:middle line:90%
There's no proof for it.

00:55:02.430 --> 00:55:04.310 align:middle line:90%
But that's the going mythology.

00:55:04.310 --> 00:55:07.400 align:middle line:84%
And so these studies
say otherwise.

00:55:07.400 --> 00:55:10.980 align:middle line:84%
They say that consciousness
can do things in the world

00:55:10.980 --> 00:55:13.590 align:middle line:90%
that brains can't do.

00:55:13.590 --> 00:55:17.220 align:middle line:84%
Brains stay put in the
cranium, in the skull.

00:55:17.220 --> 00:55:20.740 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness can acquire
information at a distance.

00:55:20.740 --> 00:55:22.600 align:middle line:84%
For example, in
remote healing, it

00:55:22.600 --> 00:55:26.090 align:middle line:84%
can insert information at
a distance into the world.

00:55:26.090 --> 00:55:29.190 align:middle line:84%
You can't explain this by
just equating consciousness

00:55:29.190 --> 00:55:30.920 align:middle line:90%
with the brain.

00:55:30.920 --> 00:55:34.170 align:middle line:84%
Taking these leads,
many academicians

00:55:34.170 --> 00:55:35.800 align:middle line:84%
from these various
fields now are

00:55:35.800 --> 00:55:39.620 align:middle line:84%
saying that consciousness
is independent of the brain.

00:55:39.620 --> 00:55:41.830 align:middle line:90%
It may work through the brain.

00:55:41.830 --> 00:55:44.040 align:middle line:90%
There's no debate about that.

00:55:44.040 --> 00:55:47.380 align:middle line:84%
But you can't understand
how consciousness operates

00:55:47.380 --> 00:55:51.220 align:middle line:84%
in our lives by just saying
it's a function of the neurons.

00:55:51.220 --> 00:55:52.360 align:middle line:90%
It just doesn't work.

00:55:52.360 --> 00:55:53.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No longer.

00:55:53.220 --> 00:55:56.740 align:middle line:84%
There's so much not only
curiosity about this,

00:55:56.740 --> 00:55:58.660 align:middle line:84%
the military's
using this in terms

00:55:58.660 --> 00:56:04.130 align:middle line:84%
of a valid way of discovering
where certain people are.

00:56:04.130 --> 00:56:07.970 align:middle line:84%
And yeah, it's very, very
well researched at this point.

00:56:07.970 --> 00:56:11.230 align:middle line:84%
And it's used currently
in our society now.

00:56:11.230 --> 00:56:12.560 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Oh, absolutely.

00:56:12.560 --> 00:56:15.237 align:middle line:84%
I think it's used
undercover in medicine, too.

00:56:15.237 --> 00:56:15.820 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Is it?

00:56:15.820 --> 00:56:19.187 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I know skeptics
who just won't go there

00:56:19.187 --> 00:56:21.020 align:middle line:84%
in terms of what you
and I have been talking

00:56:21.020 --> 00:56:24.450 align:middle line:84%
about who nonetheless,
in my opinion,

00:56:24.450 --> 00:56:28.990 align:middle line:84%
use these extraordinary
ways of knowing

00:56:28.990 --> 00:56:31.250 align:middle line:90%
without even thinking about it.

00:56:31.250 --> 00:56:33.300 align:middle line:90%
I'll just give you one example.

00:56:33.300 --> 00:56:36.590 align:middle line:84%
I had a couple of
professors in medical school

00:56:36.590 --> 00:56:40.810 align:middle line:84%
who were able to make diagnoses
in ways they couldn't even

00:56:40.810 --> 00:56:42.480 align:middle line:90%
explain.

00:56:42.480 --> 00:56:44.750 align:middle line:84%
After they were able to
make a complex diagnosis,

00:56:44.750 --> 00:56:47.430 align:middle line:84%
on one occasion, I went up
to one of them and I said,

00:56:47.430 --> 00:56:49.610 align:middle line:84%
how did you get
from A to B to C?

00:56:49.610 --> 00:56:52.500 align:middle line:90%
How did you make this diagnosis?

00:56:52.500 --> 00:56:54.330 align:middle line:90%
And he had no explanation.

00:56:54.330 --> 00:56:59.800 align:middle line:84%
He said, oh, Larry,
it's just experience.

00:56:59.800 --> 00:57:01.489 align:middle line:90%
That was really helpful.

00:57:01.489 --> 00:57:02.780 align:middle line:90%
I mean, there's no explanation.

00:57:02.780 --> 00:57:06.810 align:middle line:84%
So what I think a lot of these
really skilled diagnosticians

00:57:06.810 --> 00:57:11.180 align:middle line:84%
do is to use ways of knowing
that are not rational,

00:57:11.180 --> 00:57:14.800 align:middle line:84%
that you can't figure out in
terms of intellectual analysis.

00:57:14.800 --> 00:57:18.120 align:middle line:84%
And they just sort of
accept it as just part

00:57:18.120 --> 00:57:20.150 align:middle line:90%
of their equipment.

00:57:20.150 --> 00:57:22.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But they have been
scientifically quantified.

00:57:22.720 --> 00:57:25.040 align:middle line:84%
And there have
been studies on it.

00:57:25.040 --> 00:57:27.700 align:middle line:84%
So it does-- you
can validate it.

00:57:27.700 --> 00:57:29.060 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Well, you can.

00:57:29.060 --> 00:57:31.000 align:middle line:84%
Interestingly,
though, some people

00:57:31.000 --> 00:57:34.640 align:middle line:84%
become so self-identified
with this totally material way

00:57:34.640 --> 00:57:37.850 align:middle line:84%
of looking at things
that they don't

00:57:37.850 --> 00:57:39.900 align:middle line:90%
want to look at the studies.

00:57:39.900 --> 00:57:45.290 align:middle line:84%
I have a perverse habit
of collecting comments

00:57:45.290 --> 00:57:48.010 align:middle line:84%
from skeptics that
illustrate their refusal

00:57:48.010 --> 00:57:49.570 align:middle line:90%
to look at the data.

00:57:49.570 --> 00:57:51.580 align:middle line:90%
My favorite one is this.

00:57:51.580 --> 00:57:55.590 align:middle line:84%
One guy said, this
is the sort of thing

00:57:55.590 --> 00:57:58.772 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't believe
even if it were true.

00:57:58.772 --> 00:57:59.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS] That's good.

00:57:59.980 --> 00:58:01.610 align:middle line:84%
You told me a study
about nurses--

00:58:01.610 --> 00:58:04.020 align:middle line:84%
I mean, a story
about nurses that

00:58:04.020 --> 00:58:08.300 align:middle line:84%
went to go get a
therapeutic touch class.

00:58:08.300 --> 00:58:09.730 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's right.

00:58:09.730 --> 00:58:10.620 align:middle line:90%
My wife is a nurse.

00:58:10.620 --> 00:58:13.540 align:middle line:84%
And she was involved in
this and told me this story.

00:58:13.540 --> 00:58:17.000 align:middle line:84%
This happened at a
huge Dallas hospital.

00:58:17.000 --> 00:58:19.180 align:middle line:84%
Many nurses are very
open to these ways

00:58:19.180 --> 00:58:23.870 align:middle line:84%
of knowing and distant
healing and so on.

00:58:23.870 --> 00:58:28.470 align:middle line:84%
And so the nurse community at
the hospital sort of banded

00:58:28.470 --> 00:58:29.890 align:middle line:84%
together and went
off one weekend

00:58:29.890 --> 00:58:34.030 align:middle line:84%
to take the course in
healing touch or Reiki.

00:58:34.030 --> 00:58:36.710 align:middle line:84%
I can't remember exactly
what the technique was.

00:58:36.710 --> 00:58:39.262 align:middle line:84%
But the director of
nursing was infuriated.

00:58:39.262 --> 00:58:40.720 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That they
took this course.

00:58:40.720 --> 00:58:42.030 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: That they went
off and took the course

00:58:42.030 --> 00:58:43.500 align:middle line:90%
in distant healing.

00:58:43.500 --> 00:58:46.850 align:middle line:84%
And so when the nurses came
back to work Monday morning,

00:58:46.850 --> 00:58:49.640 align:middle line:84%
the director of nursing
had made this huge sign

00:58:49.640 --> 00:58:52.950 align:middle line:84%
and posted in the nursing
department which said,

00:58:52.950 --> 00:58:56.990 align:middle line:84%
"There will be no healing
in this hospital."

00:58:56.990 --> 00:58:58.817 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Oh, can you
imagine seeing that?

00:58:58.817 --> 00:59:00.400 align:middle line:84%
You walk in, there
will be no healing.

00:59:00.400 --> 00:59:02.600 align:middle line:90%
That's what the hospital does.

00:59:02.600 --> 00:59:05.860 align:middle line:84%
That's what you're there to
do is to heal, to get better.

00:59:05.860 --> 00:59:07.080 align:middle line:90%
That's interesting.

00:59:07.080 --> 00:59:09.600 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: A related
instant illustrating

00:59:09.600 --> 00:59:12.630 align:middle line:84%
the obstreperous nature
of some people in medicine

00:59:12.630 --> 00:59:14.730 align:middle line:84%
toward this sort
of stuff, my wife,

00:59:14.730 --> 00:59:18.630 align:middle line:84%
who is a pioneer in nursing
for this sort of thing,

00:59:18.630 --> 00:59:22.920 align:middle line:84%
Barbara-- has written many
books about this-- was invited

00:59:22.920 --> 00:59:28.580 align:middle line:84%
to give a lecture to a major
hospital in another city.

00:59:28.580 --> 00:59:32.460 align:middle line:84%
But when the people who
invited her discovered

00:59:32.460 --> 00:59:36.120 align:middle line:84%
that she was going to
talk about healing,

00:59:36.120 --> 00:59:38.500 align:middle line:84%
wrote her a
dis-invitation, saying,

00:59:38.500 --> 00:59:41.010 align:middle line:90%
well, we've thought this over.

00:59:41.010 --> 00:59:43.640 align:middle line:84%
We think we can't
invite you just yet.

00:59:43.640 --> 00:59:50.990 align:middle line:84%
But we plan to re-invite you
when we get into healing.

00:59:50.990 --> 00:59:55.500 align:middle line:84%
So Barbara, my wife, said, I
wonder what they're into now.

00:59:55.500 --> 00:59:57.470 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, what is
it that they're doing?

00:59:57.470 --> 00:59:57.650 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: What is
it that they're

00:59:57.650 --> 00:59:57.810 align:middle line:90%
doing now if not healing?

00:59:57.810 --> 01:00:00.270 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what is the
bottom line of all of this?

01:00:00.270 --> 01:00:03.510 align:middle line:84%
How can we use this
in our practical life?

01:00:03.510 --> 01:00:04.470 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Yeah.

01:00:04.470 --> 01:00:08.140 align:middle line:84%
Well I think this
is highly practical.

01:00:08.140 --> 01:00:10.610 align:middle line:84%
We've talked about
people knowing and doing

01:00:10.610 --> 01:00:14.590 align:middle line:84%
something about diseases,
incipient diseases,

01:00:14.590 --> 01:00:16.790 align:middle line:84%
before they show up,
like the breast biopsy

01:00:16.790 --> 01:00:18.980 align:middle line:84%
that the woman just
knew was there.

01:00:18.980 --> 01:00:22.000 align:middle line:84%
And also the remote
healing studies.

01:00:22.000 --> 01:00:24.491 align:middle line:90%
This is practical stuff.

01:00:24.491 --> 01:00:26.960 align:middle line:84%
I think that there's
a point, however,

01:00:26.960 --> 01:00:29.170 align:middle line:84%
where this gets
beyond being just

01:00:29.170 --> 01:00:33.830 align:middle line:84%
another tool in our black
bag of medical opportunities.

01:00:33.830 --> 01:00:37.970 align:middle line:84%
And I think it has to do with
the nature of consciousness.

01:00:37.970 --> 01:00:41.040 align:middle line:84%
What these studies
show us is that there

01:00:41.040 --> 01:00:43.640 align:middle line:84%
is some aspect of
who we are that

01:00:43.640 --> 01:00:47.582 align:middle line:84%
can operate outside
the here and now.

01:00:47.582 --> 01:00:49.290 align:middle line:84%
We can operate, we
can insert information

01:00:49.290 --> 01:00:52.160 align:middle line:90%
at a distance, remote healing.

01:00:52.160 --> 01:00:54.130 align:middle line:84%
We can know things
before they happen.

01:00:54.130 --> 01:00:56.970 align:middle line:84%
These are the premonitions
that we've touched on.

01:00:56.970 --> 01:00:59.260 align:middle line:84%
And so there's some
aspect of consciousness

01:00:59.260 --> 01:01:03.500 align:middle line:84%
that is just not confined
to the physical body.

01:01:03.500 --> 01:01:08.020 align:middle line:84%
I call this non-local
behaviors of consciousness.

01:01:08.020 --> 01:01:10.280 align:middle line:90%
I call it the non-local mind.

01:01:10.280 --> 01:01:12.500 align:middle line:84%
Non-local is a term that's
barred from physics,

01:01:12.500 --> 01:01:16.220 align:middle line:84%
but it essentially
means infinitude.

01:01:16.220 --> 01:01:20.500 align:middle line:84%
If something's non-local, it's
infinite in space and time.

01:01:20.500 --> 01:01:23.480 align:middle line:84%
Now, viewers can go
read about non-locality,

01:01:23.480 --> 01:01:26.740 align:middle line:84%
but what you will
determine in a heartbeat is

01:01:26.740 --> 01:01:31.620 align:middle line:84%
that if something's non-local,
it's eternal and immortal.

01:01:31.620 --> 01:01:33.850 align:middle line:90%
It's infinite in time.

01:01:33.850 --> 01:01:36.970 align:middle line:84%
If something's infinite in
time, it means it lasts forever.

01:01:36.970 --> 01:01:39.840 align:middle line:84%
So what these studies
do is to point

01:01:39.840 --> 01:01:44.160 align:middle line:84%
like an arrow toward an
infinite, immortal, eternal

01:01:44.160 --> 01:01:46.260 align:middle line:90%
aspect of consciousness.

01:01:46.260 --> 01:01:49.810 align:middle line:84%
I think this is a pretty
nice realization, frankly.

01:01:49.810 --> 01:01:51.510 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It gets into--
where my mind is

01:01:51.510 --> 01:01:54.430 align:middle line:84%
going is if that is
true, then what can you

01:01:54.430 --> 01:01:56.120 align:middle line:90%
create beyond that?

01:01:56.120 --> 01:01:59.450 align:middle line:84%
How can you, of course,
intentionally create healing

01:01:59.450 --> 01:02:02.520 align:middle line:84%
in yourself, intentionally
create healing in others,

01:02:02.520 --> 01:02:06.810 align:middle line:84%
intentionally create
almost anything, as long

01:02:06.810 --> 01:02:08.330 align:middle line:90%
as it's ecological?

01:02:08.330 --> 01:02:11.710 align:middle line:84%
Can it be used for
the reverse effects?

01:02:11.710 --> 01:02:14.235 align:middle line:84%
Can people create ill will
with this intentionality,

01:02:14.235 --> 01:02:17.071 align:middle line:90%
this consciousness?

01:02:17.071 --> 01:02:18.820 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well that's
a rational question.

01:02:18.820 --> 01:02:21.570 align:middle line:84%
And it's a question that
always occurs to people.

01:02:21.570 --> 01:02:24.720 align:middle line:84%
If I can use my consciousness
in positive ways,

01:02:24.720 --> 01:02:26.820 align:middle line:84%
can I use it in negative
ways, for example

01:02:26.820 --> 01:02:28.110 align:middle line:90%
to harm people and so on?

01:02:28.110 --> 01:02:29.460 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:02:29.460 --> 01:02:32.680 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: There are
no studies in humans

01:02:32.680 --> 01:02:36.750 align:middle line:84%
to look at this possibility
of harming other people.

01:02:36.750 --> 01:02:38.640 align:middle line:84%
Because those kind of
studies are illegal.

01:02:38.640 --> 01:02:43.870 align:middle line:84%
You cannot do a scientific study
whose end result is to harm.

01:02:43.870 --> 01:02:48.630 align:middle line:84%
But what you can do is to test
this possibility on non-humans.

01:02:48.630 --> 01:02:52.250 align:middle line:84%
And people have been able to
work this both ways in animals

01:02:52.250 --> 01:02:55.810 align:middle line:84%
and plants and
microbes and so on.

01:02:55.810 --> 01:02:57.730 align:middle line:84%
For example, there are
a series of studies

01:02:57.730 --> 01:03:02.360 align:middle line:84%
show that people can perk up
the growth rates positively

01:03:02.360 --> 01:03:07.290 align:middle line:84%
in this group of bacteria
and not the control group.

01:03:07.290 --> 01:03:11.230 align:middle line:84%
And they can be given different
instructions, which say,

01:03:11.230 --> 01:03:13.070 align:middle line:84%
I don't want you to
make them grow quicker.

01:03:13.070 --> 01:03:15.701 align:middle line:84%
I want you to harm them,
make them grow slower

01:03:15.701 --> 01:03:16.450 align:middle line:90%
than the controls.

01:03:16.450 --> 01:03:17.533 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The bad bacterias.

01:03:17.533 --> 01:03:18.530 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's right.

01:03:18.530 --> 01:03:20.310 align:middle line:84%
And so people can
operate this either way.

01:03:20.310 --> 01:03:22.120 align:middle line:84%
This clearly, it
seems to me, shows

01:03:22.120 --> 01:03:25.940 align:middle line:84%
that people can cause
living organisms

01:03:25.940 --> 01:03:29.760 align:middle line:90%
to flourish or to be harmed.

01:03:29.760 --> 01:03:31.970 align:middle line:90%
This is what the data show.

01:03:31.970 --> 01:03:35.390 align:middle line:84%
And so you wonder, why
do we have this ability

01:03:35.390 --> 01:03:37.280 align:middle line:90%
to help and harm?

01:03:37.280 --> 01:03:39.880 align:middle line:84%
And I think that
there's a solid reason.

01:03:39.880 --> 01:03:43.247 align:middle line:84%
And if you think about when
people have an infection.

01:03:43.247 --> 01:03:43.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:03:43.830 --> 01:03:45.621 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Let's say
pneumococcal pneumonia,

01:03:45.621 --> 01:03:50.250 align:middle line:84%
which kills tens of thousands
of elderly people every year.

01:03:50.250 --> 01:03:51.930 align:middle line:84%
If you were praying
for your grandmother

01:03:51.930 --> 01:03:55.570 align:middle line:84%
to get well from
penumococcal pneumonia,

01:03:55.570 --> 01:03:58.147 align:middle line:84%
you would not be praying for
those bacteria to flourish.

01:03:58.147 --> 01:03:58.730 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:03:58.730 --> 01:03:59.070 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Right?

01:03:59.070 --> 01:04:00.236 align:middle line:90%
You would want to harm them.

01:04:00.236 --> 01:04:01.780 align:middle line:84%
You probably want
even to kill them.

01:04:01.780 --> 01:04:02.220 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:04:02.220 --> 01:04:04.261 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I mean, that's
why we give antibiotics.

01:04:04.261 --> 01:04:06.310 align:middle line:84%
We want to kill
those suckers, right?

01:04:06.310 --> 01:04:08.300 align:middle line:84%
And so there are
certain situations

01:04:08.300 --> 01:04:12.510 align:middle line:84%
where it might come in really
handy to be able to harm

01:04:12.510 --> 01:04:16.470 align:middle line:84%
certain living things,
like pathogenic bacteria.

01:04:16.470 --> 01:04:19.850 align:middle line:84%
And if you think about
using your consciousness

01:04:19.850 --> 01:04:23.510 align:middle line:84%
to harm cells, well if
somebody has cancer,

01:04:23.510 --> 01:04:26.767 align:middle line:84%
you probably really want
to kill those cancer cells.

01:04:26.767 --> 01:04:27.350 align:middle line:90%
So it may be--

01:04:27.350 --> 01:04:28.180 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's what
the chemotherapy does.

01:04:28.180 --> 01:04:28.720 align:middle line:90%
Yes, yes.

01:04:28.720 --> 01:04:30.170 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's exactly right.

01:04:30.170 --> 01:04:31.780 align:middle line:84%
So there are
situations where you

01:04:31.780 --> 01:04:33.570 align:middle line:84%
can imagine it would
be a good thing

01:04:33.570 --> 01:04:38.010 align:middle line:84%
to be able to harm living
things, pathogenic bacteria,

01:04:38.010 --> 01:04:40.190 align:middle line:90%
cancer cells among them.

01:04:40.190 --> 01:04:42.830 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so this-- so
I mean, we're acting as if

01:04:42.830 --> 01:04:46.130 align:middle line:84%
and we're talking as
if this really does

01:04:46.130 --> 01:04:51.060 align:middle line:84%
work, this whole field
of, as it's been called,

01:04:51.060 --> 01:04:54.840 align:middle line:84%
quantum entanglement really,
absolutely does work.

01:04:54.840 --> 01:04:56.920 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well quantum
entanglement has emerged--

01:04:56.920 --> 01:04:58.810 align:middle line:84%
it's one of the
most popular ideas

01:04:58.810 --> 01:05:01.630 align:middle line:84%
about how this
might be understood.

01:05:01.630 --> 01:05:05.110 align:middle line:84%
And it goes back to
observations about 30 years

01:05:05.110 --> 01:05:09.280 align:middle line:84%
ago in what are called quantum
physics experiments where you

01:05:09.280 --> 01:05:12.020 align:middle line:84%
take two particles that are
in contact, separate them,

01:05:12.020 --> 01:05:13.940 align:middle line:84%
even to the opposite
ends of the universe,

01:05:13.940 --> 01:05:17.300 align:middle line:84%
and when you change one,
the other changes instantly

01:05:17.300 --> 01:05:18.720 align:middle line:90%
and to the same degree.

01:05:18.720 --> 01:05:21.070 align:middle line:90%
How is this possible?

01:05:21.070 --> 01:05:22.080 align:middle line:90%
There's no contact.

01:05:22.080 --> 01:05:23.360 align:middle line:90%
It happens instantly.

01:05:23.360 --> 01:05:26.690 align:middle line:84%
There's no time for a signal
to go from one to the other.

01:05:26.690 --> 01:05:30.350 align:middle line:84%
So they behave as if
they are a single entity,

01:05:30.350 --> 01:05:31.577 align:middle line:90%
even though they're apart.

01:05:31.577 --> 01:05:33.035 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Now, I
remember-- the story

01:05:33.035 --> 01:05:36.200 align:middle line:84%
you told me was
about somebody was

01:05:36.200 --> 01:05:38.300 align:middle line:90%
watching images in a monitor.

01:05:38.300 --> 01:05:40.305 align:middle line:84%
And they were being
monitored in the next room.

01:05:40.305 --> 01:05:42.430 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell me a little
bit about the neurons that

01:05:42.430 --> 01:05:44.424 align:middle line:84%
were monitored as a
reaction of the images?

01:05:44.424 --> 01:05:45.090 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Right.

01:05:45.090 --> 01:05:49.990 align:middle line:84%
What this study actually did
was to take human brain cells,

01:05:49.990 --> 01:05:55.520 align:middle line:84%
neurons, and grow them
in a cell culture dish.

01:05:55.520 --> 01:05:58.430 align:middle line:84%
And so what you have
here are brain cells,

01:05:58.430 --> 01:06:01.930 align:middle line:84%
brain tissue, over
here and over here.

01:06:01.930 --> 01:06:03.930 align:middle line:84%
And they're put in
a lead-lined box

01:06:03.930 --> 01:06:05.790 align:middle line:84%
so that there's
no communication.

01:06:05.790 --> 01:06:08.150 align:middle line:84%
They're shielded
from each other.

01:06:08.150 --> 01:06:10.760 align:middle line:84%
And what happens is that
if you shine a laser

01:06:10.760 --> 01:06:17.060 align:middle line:84%
beam on one group of them,
they change, and instantly

01:06:17.060 --> 01:06:20.310 align:middle line:84%
the other distant,
shielded neurons

01:06:20.310 --> 01:06:22.740 align:middle line:90%
change to the same degree.

01:06:22.740 --> 01:06:26.370 align:middle line:84%
So somehow they're communicating
even though they can't.

01:06:26.370 --> 01:06:29.920 align:middle line:84%
They're shielded from all
electromagnetic signals.

01:06:29.920 --> 01:06:34.280 align:middle line:84%
They have no known connections
between each other.

01:06:34.280 --> 01:06:37.790 align:middle line:84%
But they behave as if
they're still united.

01:06:37.790 --> 01:06:42.070 align:middle line:84%
Now this is entanglement
at the cellular level.

01:06:42.070 --> 01:06:44.660 align:middle line:84%
We're not talking
photons or electrons.

01:06:44.660 --> 01:06:46.992 align:middle line:84%
We're talking
human brain tissue.

01:06:46.992 --> 01:06:49.450 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And the same thing was
done if the brain tissue was

01:06:49.450 --> 01:06:51.922 align:middle line:84%
put into another room,
another building.

01:06:51.922 --> 01:06:52.880 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's right.

01:06:52.880 --> 01:06:54.490 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Another state.

01:06:54.490 --> 01:06:57.600 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And here's where this
becomes really interesting.

01:06:57.600 --> 01:07:00.760 align:middle line:84%
You can take people
now, having demonstrated

01:07:00.760 --> 01:07:03.620 align:middle line:84%
that brain tissue can be
connected at a distance,

01:07:03.620 --> 01:07:05.800 align:middle line:90%
and you can separate the people.

01:07:05.800 --> 01:07:09.580 align:middle line:84%
And you can hook them
both up to an EEG machine

01:07:09.580 --> 01:07:14.500 align:middle line:84%
or an fMRI, imaging
fancy piece of equipment.

01:07:14.500 --> 01:07:18.610 align:middle line:84%
And you can shine a light
in the eyes of one person,

01:07:18.610 --> 01:07:24.050 align:middle line:84%
making the EEG jump, and
instantly the other EEG

01:07:24.050 --> 01:07:26.550 align:middle line:84%
registers the same change,
even though there's

01:07:26.550 --> 01:07:28.650 align:middle line:84%
no connection between
these people at all.

01:07:28.650 --> 01:07:29.790 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: No communication
that you're

01:07:29.790 --> 01:07:31.310 align:middle line:84%
going to get a light
shined in-- nothing.

01:07:31.310 --> 01:07:31.820 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: No, no, no.

01:07:31.820 --> 01:07:32.486 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Nothing.

01:07:32.486 --> 01:07:35.520 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And somehow
there's a connection.

01:07:35.520 --> 01:07:39.220 align:middle line:84%
This defies everything we know
about conventional science.

01:07:39.220 --> 01:07:40.050 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Absolutely.

01:07:40.050 --> 01:07:42.508 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: But you know what is
interesting about the people

01:07:42.508 --> 01:07:45.150 align:middle line:84%
who do demonstrate the
changes at a distance

01:07:45.150 --> 01:07:47.320 align:middle line:84%
as if they're
connected, they usually

01:07:47.320 --> 01:07:50.030 align:middle line:84%
are very empathic
with each other.

01:07:50.030 --> 01:07:52.510 align:middle line:84%
They usually are people
who know each other

01:07:52.510 --> 01:07:55.220 align:middle line:84%
and have a loving
heart connection.

01:07:55.220 --> 01:07:58.740 align:middle line:84%
And this has been worked
out in many studies that

01:07:58.740 --> 01:08:03.800 align:middle line:84%
look at the way the
connection may be mediated.

01:08:03.800 --> 01:08:06.350 align:middle line:84%
This really gets back
to the healing work,

01:08:06.350 --> 01:08:09.760 align:middle line:84%
because all of the healers
whom I have interviewed

01:08:09.760 --> 01:08:12.980 align:middle line:84%
and whom I have asked,
how do you do this?

01:08:12.980 --> 01:08:16.260 align:middle line:90%
What makes this work?

01:08:16.260 --> 01:08:19.380 align:middle line:84%
If you take it away,
and it won't work,

01:08:19.380 --> 01:08:20.920 align:middle line:90%
what would that thing be?

01:08:20.920 --> 01:08:22.460 align:middle line:90%
And they all say love.

01:08:22.460 --> 01:08:24.649 align:middle line:90%
They say caring.

01:08:24.649 --> 01:08:26.790 align:middle line:90%
You've got to have empathy.

01:08:26.790 --> 01:08:29.521 align:middle line:84%
Some will use a term like,
well, you've just got to care.

01:08:29.521 --> 01:08:31.229 align:middle line:84%
You've just got to
feel it in your heart.

01:08:31.229 --> 01:08:32.090 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But some
of these healers

01:08:32.090 --> 01:08:33.880 align:middle line:84%
don't even know the subjects
that they're healing.

01:08:33.880 --> 01:08:35.080 align:middle line:84%
So they don't have
a relationship.

01:08:35.080 --> 01:08:36.038 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's right.

01:08:36.038 --> 01:08:38.439 align:middle line:84%
But if they have a
relationship, the effect

01:08:38.439 --> 01:08:40.094 align:middle line:84%
seems to be even
more pronounced.

01:08:40.094 --> 01:08:41.010 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Even stronger.

01:08:41.010 --> 01:08:42.479 align:middle line:84%
Has it ever been
effective on people

01:08:42.479 --> 01:08:43.800 align:middle line:84%
that don't have
the relationship?

01:08:43.800 --> 01:08:44.540 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Oh, yes.

01:08:44.540 --> 01:08:44.790 align:middle line:90%
It has.

01:08:44.790 --> 01:08:45.415 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It has?

01:08:45.415 --> 01:08:47.899 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Healing
has been demonstrated

01:08:47.899 --> 01:08:51.859 align:middle line:84%
in these double-blind studies
when healers who don't even

01:08:51.859 --> 01:08:55.560 align:middle line:90%
know the recipient are involved.

01:08:55.560 --> 01:08:56.210 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

01:08:56.210 --> 01:08:57.020 align:middle line:90%
And it's effective?

01:08:57.020 --> 01:08:57.859 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: It is.

01:08:57.859 --> 01:09:00.470 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is, I think that
almost all of these studies

01:09:00.470 --> 01:09:04.950 align:middle line:84%
would be even more effective if
they use healers who actually

01:09:04.950 --> 01:09:08.490 align:middle line:90%
knew who they were praying for.

01:09:08.490 --> 01:09:12.529 align:middle line:84%
You see, in real life, we
say something like, well,

01:09:12.529 --> 01:09:14.464 align:middle line:84%
we pray for our
loved ones, right?

01:09:14.464 --> 01:09:16.380 align:middle line:84%
I mean, you hear people
say this all the time.

01:09:16.380 --> 01:09:17.359 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes, yes.

01:09:17.359 --> 01:09:19.750 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And there's a
lot of wisdom in that.

01:09:19.750 --> 01:09:20.729 align:middle line:90%
You love them.

01:09:20.729 --> 01:09:22.819 align:middle line:84%
That means you know
them, almost always.

01:09:22.819 --> 01:09:24.430 align:middle line:90%
You know who you're praying for.

01:09:24.430 --> 01:09:27.470 align:middle line:84%
And also you pray
unconditionally for them.

01:09:27.470 --> 01:09:29.960 align:middle line:84%
You don't hold out
prayer as a maybe.

01:09:29.960 --> 01:09:32.010 align:middle line:84%
I think I might pray for
you, but I'm not sure.

01:09:32.010 --> 01:09:33.260 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is a
double-blind experiment.

01:09:33.260 --> 01:09:33.710 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I'm only going
to pray a little bit.

01:09:33.710 --> 01:09:35.335 align:middle line:84%
Or I don't want you
to heal completely.

01:09:35.335 --> 01:09:35.920 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

01:09:35.920 --> 01:09:37.140 align:middle line:90%
There's no judgement in it.

01:09:37.140 --> 01:09:39.279 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: But you get
your heart into it.

01:09:39.279 --> 01:09:43.010 align:middle line:84%
And so that's why I think some
of the spontaneous healings

01:09:43.010 --> 01:09:45.270 align:middle line:84%
that we see in real
life, where people pray

01:09:45.270 --> 01:09:48.529 align:middle line:84%
for another person and
the disease goes away,

01:09:48.529 --> 01:09:52.540 align:middle line:84%
I think that's where you see
the power of prayer jacked up

01:09:52.540 --> 01:09:53.980 align:middle line:90%
to a really high level.

01:09:53.980 --> 01:09:54.980 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's enormous.

01:09:54.980 --> 01:09:56.000 align:middle line:84%
I mean, then we're going
to talk a little bit

01:09:56.000 --> 01:09:58.320 align:middle line:84%
about the studies on
spontaneous remissions.

01:09:58.320 --> 01:10:00.830 align:middle line:84%
But I'm thinking about
this in a practical sense

01:10:00.830 --> 01:10:02.870 align:middle line:90%
and in a humanitarian sense.

01:10:02.870 --> 01:10:06.600 align:middle line:84%
I mean, when we pray for
people who are hungry,

01:10:06.600 --> 01:10:09.580 align:middle line:84%
when you pray for people
that are starving,

01:10:09.580 --> 01:10:15.510 align:middle line:84%
that are destitute, that prayer
in large numbers of people,

01:10:15.510 --> 01:10:16.386 align:middle line:90%
really is effective.

01:10:16.386 --> 01:10:17.760 align:middle line:84%
That's what we're
learning today.

01:10:17.760 --> 01:10:19.551 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, that's
what we're learning.

01:10:19.551 --> 01:10:21.280 align:middle line:90%
And we're not fooling ourselves.

01:10:21.280 --> 01:10:24.270 align:middle line:84%
One thing that we get
out of these experiments

01:10:24.270 --> 01:10:28.830 align:middle line:84%
is proof that when we
assume that my thoughts

01:10:28.830 --> 01:10:31.790 align:middle line:84%
and my compassionate intentions
make a difference out there

01:10:31.790 --> 01:10:34.370 align:middle line:84%
in the world,
that's not fantasy.

01:10:34.370 --> 01:10:36.300 align:middle line:84%
That's the ultimate
value of these studies.

01:10:36.300 --> 01:10:39.200 align:middle line:84%
They show that we're
not fooling ourselves

01:10:39.200 --> 01:10:41.030 align:middle line:84%
when we talk about
the ability of people

01:10:41.030 --> 01:10:43.910 align:middle line:84%
to positively influence
others at a distance.

01:10:43.910 --> 01:10:46.410 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But why is there,
then, still starvation

01:10:46.410 --> 01:10:48.870 align:middle line:84%
and child prostitution
and destitution?

01:10:48.870 --> 01:10:52.440 align:middle line:90%


01:10:52.440 --> 01:10:54.000 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: If I were
able answer that,

01:10:54.000 --> 01:10:56.560 align:middle line:84%
I think I'd be
awarded a Nobel Prize.

01:10:56.560 --> 01:10:59.560 align:middle line:84%
These are the great things
that we struggle with.

01:10:59.560 --> 01:11:04.140 align:middle line:84%
We can always say that if we
were not praying and intending

01:11:04.140 --> 01:11:06.670 align:middle line:84%
a better situation
through prayers

01:11:06.670 --> 01:11:08.750 align:middle line:84%
or healing intentions
or whatever,

01:11:08.750 --> 01:11:10.880 align:middle line:90%
that situations would be worse.

01:11:10.880 --> 01:11:12.850 align:middle line:84%
I know that's not a very
satisfactory answer.

01:11:12.850 --> 01:11:15.836 align:middle line:84%
But I think that's one
of those questions that--

01:11:15.836 --> 01:11:18.210 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is not scientifically
quantifiable at this point.

01:11:18.210 --> 01:11:19.660 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I don't know
how to approach that.

01:11:19.660 --> 01:11:20.243 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:11:20.243 --> 01:11:24.620 align:middle line:84%
But what we can approach is the
ideas of spontaneous remission

01:11:24.620 --> 01:11:25.810 align:middle line:90%
and how this has worked.

01:11:25.810 --> 01:11:28.410 align:middle line:84%
Now, we mentioned there's
some studies on this,

01:11:28.410 --> 01:11:32.820 align:middle line:84%
on spontaneous remission
and how many cases

01:11:32.820 --> 01:11:36.497 align:middle line:84%
it actually worked on and
how many it didn't work on.

01:11:36.497 --> 01:11:38.080 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: This is
an interesting area,

01:11:38.080 --> 01:11:41.470 align:middle line:84%
because most physicians
are taught, as I was,

01:11:41.470 --> 01:11:45.880 align:middle line:84%
that spontaneous
remissions are really rare.

01:11:45.880 --> 01:11:50.520 align:middle line:84%
I was told that you'll probably
go through your entire career

01:11:50.520 --> 01:11:53.020 align:middle line:84%
without ever seeing
one of these things.

01:11:53.020 --> 01:11:54.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:11:54.250 --> 01:11:57.330 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I think that's
just flat out wrong.

01:11:57.330 --> 01:12:01.290 align:middle line:84%
Several years ago, Carol
Hirshberg and Brenna Regan

01:12:01.290 --> 01:12:03.600 align:middle line:84%
did a literature search
from around the world

01:12:03.600 --> 01:12:06.650 align:middle line:84%
in many languages and dozens
of scientific journals

01:12:06.650 --> 01:12:09.470 align:middle line:84%
and came up with
over 3,000 cases that

01:12:09.470 --> 01:12:12.450 align:middle line:84%
have been published in the
medical literature where

01:12:12.450 --> 01:12:16.200 align:middle line:84%
the disease just absolutely went
away, either with no therapy

01:12:16.200 --> 01:12:18.160 align:middle line:84%
or with such piddly
therapy that you couldn't

01:12:18.160 --> 01:12:20.450 align:middle line:84%
attribute the cure
to the therapy.

01:12:20.450 --> 01:12:22.590 align:middle line:84%
And so this flies in
the face of the idea

01:12:22.590 --> 01:12:24.429 align:middle line:84%
that these things
are really rare.

01:12:24.429 --> 01:12:25.970 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And it also
said that they're

01:12:25.970 --> 01:12:29.145 align:middle line:84%
done in different languages,
20 different languages.

01:12:29.145 --> 01:12:30.770 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Which means
that these things

01:12:30.770 --> 01:12:32.540 align:middle line:90%
are seen all over the world.

01:12:32.540 --> 01:12:35.790 align:middle line:84%
And bear this in mind--
these things are not

01:12:35.790 --> 01:12:39.540 align:middle line:84%
usually reported, so
they're under-reported.

01:12:39.540 --> 01:12:41.230 align:middle line:84%
Doctors don't want
to write them up.

01:12:41.230 --> 01:12:42.725 align:middle line:90%
They just ignore them.

01:12:42.725 --> 01:12:43.600 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, right.

01:12:43.600 --> 01:12:46.500 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So they found
3,000 of these studies.

01:12:46.500 --> 01:12:50.330 align:middle line:84%
How many more actually
happened, would we

01:12:50.330 --> 01:12:52.545 align:middle line:84%
imagine, since they're
not usually reported?

01:12:52.545 --> 01:12:53.350 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Of course.

01:12:53.350 --> 01:12:56.260 align:middle line:84%
I mean, that could
absolutely double.

01:12:56.260 --> 01:12:58.040 align:middle line:84%
There's a specific
study that was

01:12:58.040 --> 01:13:01.556 align:middle line:90%
done about Rita Klaus, that one?

01:13:01.556 --> 01:13:02.230 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Right.

01:13:02.230 --> 01:13:04.760 align:middle line:84%
Well, Rita Klaus is my
favorite example of one

01:13:04.760 --> 01:13:08.490 align:middle line:84%
of these spontaneous
healings that just happens.

01:13:08.490 --> 01:13:12.080 align:middle line:84%
Her history is
absolutely fascinating.

01:13:12.080 --> 01:13:14.970 align:middle line:84%
She was extremely
religious as a girl.

01:13:14.970 --> 01:13:18.230 align:middle line:84%
And she received permission
to go into a convent

01:13:18.230 --> 01:13:23.870 align:middle line:84%
to become a nun earlier than
the rules ordinarily allowed.

01:13:23.870 --> 01:13:27.090 align:middle line:84%
But something
horrible happened soon

01:13:27.090 --> 01:13:28.410 align:middle line:90%
after she went to the convent.

01:13:28.410 --> 01:13:31.477 align:middle line:84%
She developed her first
symptoms of multiple sclerosis.

01:13:31.477 --> 01:13:33.060 align:middle line:84%
And this proved to
be one of the worst

01:13:33.060 --> 01:13:35.220 align:middle line:84%
cases of multiple
sclerosis you can imagine.

01:13:35.220 --> 01:13:35.750 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

01:13:35.750 --> 01:13:36.916 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: She couldn't walk.

01:13:36.916 --> 01:13:39.440 align:middle line:90%
She wound up in a wheelchair.

01:13:39.440 --> 01:13:42.210 align:middle line:84%
She could not attend to
her duties in the convent,

01:13:42.210 --> 01:13:45.710 align:middle line:84%
so she was given
dispensation from her vows

01:13:45.710 --> 01:13:47.530 align:middle line:90%
and allowed to leave.

01:13:47.530 --> 01:13:51.660 align:middle line:84%
She had to make a living, so she
went back and became a biology

01:13:51.660 --> 01:13:53.680 align:middle line:90%
teacher in high school.

01:13:53.680 --> 01:13:57.870 align:middle line:90%
And she lost her faith.

01:13:57.870 --> 01:14:03.160 align:middle line:84%
She became extremely furious,
in particular, at faith healers.

01:14:03.160 --> 01:14:06.890 align:middle line:84%
And she wanted nothing to do
with any of this spirituality

01:14:06.890 --> 01:14:08.660 align:middle line:90%
and healing business.

01:14:08.660 --> 01:14:13.370 align:middle line:84%
And there remained a little
interest in healing, however,

01:14:13.370 --> 01:14:16.070 align:middle line:84%
because she went to
Medjugorge, in Yugoslavia

01:14:16.070 --> 01:14:19.810 align:middle line:84%
at the time, where a lot of
miracles have been reported.

01:14:19.810 --> 01:14:20.980 align:middle line:90%
But she didn't get one.

01:14:20.980 --> 01:14:25.970 align:middle line:84%
She came back with no effect,
positive benefit, at all.

01:14:25.970 --> 01:14:30.840 align:middle line:84%
And so she doesn't
know what to do.

01:14:30.840 --> 01:14:34.240 align:middle line:84%
And at her wits end,
she can't stand up

01:14:34.240 --> 01:14:36.420 align:middle line:90%
without locked iron braces.

01:14:36.420 --> 01:14:39.290 align:middle line:84%
And so-- and her
doctors had predicted

01:14:39.290 --> 01:14:42.130 align:middle line:84%
that she-- this was such
a bad case it would soon

01:14:42.130 --> 01:14:44.750 align:middle line:84%
affect her mental
abilities and so on.

01:14:44.750 --> 01:14:47.320 align:middle line:90%
So one night she has a dream.

01:14:47.320 --> 01:14:52.860 align:middle line:84%
And in the dream, she sees the
Virgin Mary appear before her,

01:14:52.860 --> 01:14:59.300 align:middle line:84%
and Mary says, Rita, why don't
you just ask for a healing?

01:14:59.300 --> 01:15:04.450 align:middle line:84%
So in her dream, Rita
just asks for healing.

01:15:04.450 --> 01:15:06.890 align:middle line:84%
Actually, she had
never done this before.

01:15:06.890 --> 01:15:08.670 align:middle line:90%
So she wakes up.

01:15:08.670 --> 01:15:10.900 align:middle line:84%
The next day she's
teaching biology

01:15:10.900 --> 01:15:15.020 align:middle line:84%
in her wheelchair in
the high school class,

01:15:15.020 --> 01:15:18.810 align:middle line:84%
and she looks down and
she sees her toes moving.

01:15:18.810 --> 01:15:21.810 align:middle line:84%
And she says, well,
it's just muscle spasm.

01:15:21.810 --> 01:15:23.810 align:middle line:90%
I've had this before.

01:15:23.810 --> 01:15:28.260 align:middle line:84%
And interestingly,
her kneecaps, which

01:15:28.260 --> 01:15:31.030 align:middle line:84%
were on the outside of her knees
because the doctors had severed

01:15:31.030 --> 01:15:34.290 align:middle line:84%
the tendons to give her a little
more movement-- the kneecaps

01:15:34.290 --> 01:15:38.370 align:middle line:84%
have migrated back into
their normal position.

01:15:38.370 --> 01:15:39.789 align:middle line:90%
This is essentially impossible.

01:15:39.789 --> 01:15:40.580 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, yeah.

01:15:40.580 --> 01:15:41.996 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So what's
going on here?

01:15:41.996 --> 01:15:45.440 align:middle line:84%
And she says, I want
you to take me home.

01:15:45.440 --> 01:15:49.140 align:middle line:84%
Somebody drives her home,
helps her get her wheelchair

01:15:49.140 --> 01:15:51.510 align:middle line:90%
into the living room.

01:15:51.510 --> 01:15:53.090 align:middle line:84%
So she's sitting
there, and she says,

01:15:53.090 --> 01:15:55.520 align:middle line:84%
I'm going to put
this to the test.

01:15:55.520 --> 01:15:58.590 align:middle line:84%
She says, if something
is really happening here,

01:15:58.590 --> 01:16:00.965 align:middle line:84%
I can get out of this
wheelchair and run up

01:16:00.965 --> 01:16:04.093 align:middle line:84%
these 13 steps to
the second floor.

01:16:04.093 --> 01:16:06.440 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That was more of a test.

01:16:06.440 --> 01:16:07.940 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: This is
idiotic, really.

01:16:07.940 --> 01:16:09.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

01:16:09.250 --> 01:16:10.590 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: And she does.

01:16:10.590 --> 01:16:11.590 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: She did it?

01:16:11.590 --> 01:16:13.360 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: She did.

01:16:13.360 --> 01:16:16.200 align:middle line:90%
She ran back down the stairs.

01:16:16.200 --> 01:16:19.150 align:middle line:84%
She ran out the front
door of her house,

01:16:19.150 --> 01:16:21.670 align:middle line:84%
jumped over a little creek,
fell down and got muddy.

01:16:21.670 --> 01:16:26.210 align:middle line:84%
And she comes back
into the living room

01:16:26.210 --> 01:16:29.510 align:middle line:84%
and picks up the phone
and calls her priest.

01:16:29.510 --> 01:16:34.200 align:middle line:84%
And this poor man is-- actually,
he's kind of horrified by this.

01:16:34.200 --> 01:16:35.970 align:middle line:90%
He hadn't seen this before.

01:16:35.970 --> 01:16:39.930 align:middle line:84%
And says, Rita, lie
down, take an aspirin,

01:16:39.930 --> 01:16:41.572 align:middle line:90%
and call your doctor.

01:16:41.572 --> 01:16:42.669 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: [LAUGHS]

01:16:42.669 --> 01:16:44.710 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So he didn't
want anything to do with--

01:16:44.710 --> 01:16:44.930 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: He didn't
believe it, either.

01:16:44.930 --> 01:16:46.245 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: He didn't
believe any of this stuff.

01:16:46.245 --> 01:16:46.970 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

01:16:46.970 --> 01:16:49.280 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So she calls her
best friend, who comes over.

01:16:49.280 --> 01:16:52.080 align:middle line:84%
They enjoyed a
good cry together.

01:16:52.080 --> 01:16:55.320 align:middle line:84%
So in a couple days, her
husband takes her back

01:16:55.320 --> 01:16:56.870 align:middle line:90%
to the big hospital.

01:16:56.870 --> 01:17:00.750 align:middle line:84%
And she sees all of her
sub-specialists, the urologist,

01:17:00.750 --> 01:17:03.530 align:middle line:84%
the orthopedist, the
neurologists, and so on.

01:17:03.530 --> 01:17:07.710 align:middle line:84%
And some of them
don't believe it.

01:17:07.710 --> 01:17:11.660 align:middle line:84%
One of her doctors accused her
of having an identical twin

01:17:11.660 --> 01:17:14.610 align:middle line:84%
and playing a
practical joke on them.

01:17:14.610 --> 01:17:15.630 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh my goodness.

01:17:15.630 --> 01:17:16.960 align:middle line:90%
Because it was that shocking.

01:17:16.960 --> 01:17:17.543 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Yes.

01:17:17.543 --> 01:17:18.530 align:middle line:90%
It was that shocking.

01:17:18.530 --> 01:17:24.170 align:middle line:84%
But one of her doctors
did a neurological exam,

01:17:24.170 --> 01:17:24.920 align:middle line:90%
and it was normal.

01:17:24.920 --> 01:17:26.932 align:middle line:84%
Even the tendon
reflexes were normal.

01:17:26.932 --> 01:17:28.390 align:middle line:84%
This should not
have been possible.

01:17:28.390 --> 01:17:31.530 align:middle line:84%
Because the surgeons had
severed the tendons, right?

01:17:31.530 --> 01:17:32.890 align:middle line:90%
But now they're normal.

01:17:32.890 --> 01:17:36.090 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact, her
entire neurological examination

01:17:36.090 --> 01:17:37.896 align:middle line:90%
was normal.

01:17:37.896 --> 01:17:39.770 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This is one of
the most extreme cases

01:17:39.770 --> 01:17:40.561 align:middle line:90%
I've ever heard of.

01:17:40.561 --> 01:17:42.300 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I think
it takes the cake.

01:17:42.300 --> 01:17:44.891 align:middle line:84%
And I love this because
it's all written down.

01:17:44.891 --> 01:17:45.890 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's documented.

01:17:45.890 --> 01:17:47.970 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: A couple
of my friends who

01:17:47.970 --> 01:17:52.040 align:middle line:84%
wrote a book about this actually
went to look at her hospital

01:17:52.040 --> 01:17:54.540 align:middle line:84%
charts and the progress
notes and the whole thing.

01:17:54.540 --> 01:17:57.530 align:middle line:84%
So this is well recorded
and well documented.

01:17:57.530 --> 01:17:59.780 align:middle line:90%
But what do you do with that?

01:17:59.780 --> 01:18:02.499 align:middle line:84%
I mean, this is not
possible from the standpoint

01:18:02.499 --> 01:18:03.540 align:middle line:90%
of conventional medicine.

01:18:03.540 --> 01:18:04.220 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is it just
this one person?

01:18:04.220 --> 01:18:06.744 align:middle line:84%
Right, can it just happen
to her and not to me?

01:18:06.744 --> 01:18:08.160 align:middle line:84%
But there's
statistics around this

01:18:08.160 --> 01:18:11.640 align:middle line:84%
as well that you've accumulated
about how many people believe

01:18:11.640 --> 01:18:15.740 align:middle line:84%
here that Marc Ian
Barasch did and Hirschberg

01:18:15.740 --> 01:18:18.580 align:middle line:84%
did as well about
spontaneous remissions

01:18:18.580 --> 01:18:20.335 align:middle line:84%
and how many people
actually have

01:18:20.335 --> 01:18:22.902 align:middle line:84%
received-- have
experienced them.

01:18:22.902 --> 01:18:23.860 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's right.

01:18:23.860 --> 01:18:27.830 align:middle line:84%
This the team--
Hirshberg was one

01:18:27.830 --> 01:18:31.390 align:middle line:84%
of the team that found those
3,000 studies worldwide.

01:18:31.390 --> 01:18:35.500 align:middle line:84%
And she and Marc Barasch
interviewed around 60 people

01:18:35.500 --> 01:18:38.770 align:middle line:84%
in the United States they
could get their-- get contact

01:18:38.770 --> 01:18:42.170 align:middle line:84%
with who had actually
been written up

01:18:42.170 --> 01:18:43.780 align:middle line:90%
in the medical literature.

01:18:43.780 --> 01:18:45.294 align:middle line:84%
So they went to
these people and did

01:18:45.294 --> 01:18:46.960 align:middle line:84%
something that's never
been done before.

01:18:46.960 --> 01:18:49.410 align:middle line:90%
They said, why did you get well?

01:18:49.410 --> 01:18:50.930 align:middle line:84%
See, when these
cases are reported

01:18:50.930 --> 01:18:53.760 align:middle line:84%
in the medical literature,
you never get this.

01:18:53.760 --> 01:18:56.880 align:middle line:84%
They never ask the person why
they thought they got well.

01:18:56.880 --> 01:19:00.600 align:middle line:84%
But they did it, and you can
see that the reasons that people

01:19:00.600 --> 01:19:04.460 align:middle line:84%
give for getting well are
all over the ballpark.

01:19:04.460 --> 01:19:07.515 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's like anything
has been attributed to work.

01:19:07.515 --> 01:19:08.390 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Look at that.

01:19:08.390 --> 01:19:10.860 align:middle line:84%
The highest percentage,
though, is positive belief,

01:19:10.860 --> 01:19:12.174 align:middle line:90%
which I find very interesting.

01:19:12.174 --> 01:19:12.840 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Right.

01:19:12.840 --> 01:19:20.240 align:middle line:84%
And also prayer is right up
there close with 68% or 69%.

01:19:20.240 --> 01:19:22.700 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I don't see difference
that much in positive belief

01:19:22.700 --> 01:19:24.690 align:middle line:84%
and prayer, but
apparently there is?

01:19:24.690 --> 01:19:27.280 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I think
it's all blended together.

01:19:27.280 --> 01:19:28.550 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Me, too.

01:19:28.550 --> 01:19:30.370 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And I'm almost
certain the people

01:19:30.370 --> 01:19:35.540 align:middle line:84%
who pray with the expectation
of getting better-- that's

01:19:35.540 --> 01:19:37.210 align:middle line:90%
positive belief if you ask me.

01:19:37.210 --> 01:19:41.310 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is there a
certain way of praying?

01:19:41.310 --> 01:19:44.230 align:middle line:84%
Is there a certain way
that you recommend to pray

01:19:44.230 --> 01:19:48.282 align:middle line:84%
or that you have studied that
works better than other ways?

01:19:48.282 --> 01:19:50.240 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I've looked at
that pretty carefully.

01:19:50.240 --> 01:19:50.880 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

01:19:50.880 --> 01:19:53.830 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And
people forever have

01:19:53.830 --> 01:19:56.110 align:middle line:84%
been looking for the
right way to pray, right?

01:19:56.110 --> 01:19:56.940 align:middle line:90%
What's the formula?

01:19:56.940 --> 01:19:57.020 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:19:57.020 --> 01:19:57.180 align:middle line:90%
What do I do?

01:19:57.180 --> 01:19:58.660 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: That's
what I want to do.

01:19:58.660 --> 01:19:59.760 align:middle line:90%
That's right.

01:19:59.760 --> 01:20:02.190 align:middle line:90%
There isn't one.

01:20:02.190 --> 01:20:04.930 align:middle line:84%
If you ask people
who are good at this,

01:20:04.930 --> 01:20:09.240 align:middle line:84%
the really solid healers who
perform well in the studies,

01:20:09.240 --> 01:20:11.330 align:middle line:90%
they're all over the ballpark.

01:20:11.330 --> 01:20:14.720 align:middle line:84%
Some use "thee" and "thou,"
and some use vivid imagery.

01:20:14.720 --> 01:20:18.410 align:middle line:90%
Some try to get rid of imagery.

01:20:18.410 --> 01:20:22.330 align:middle line:84%
As we've already mentioned, some
are religious, some are not.

01:20:22.330 --> 01:20:26.590 align:middle line:84%
I know even agnostics who
use healing intentions,

01:20:26.590 --> 01:20:29.130 align:middle line:84%
but they don't want it
mixed up with religion.

01:20:29.130 --> 01:20:30.890 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you can
use visualization.

01:20:30.890 --> 01:20:32.950 align:middle line:90%
You can use meditation.

01:20:32.950 --> 01:20:33.850 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Absolutely.

01:20:33.850 --> 01:20:35.430 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Well, it has been done.

01:20:35.430 --> 01:20:37.040 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well,
it has been done.

01:20:37.040 --> 01:20:39.700 align:middle line:84%
And that's one of the strategies
that's been looked at.

01:20:39.700 --> 01:20:43.240 align:middle line:84%
I must say that early on in
the history of these peer

01:20:43.240 --> 01:20:47.480 align:middle line:84%
experiments, people tested
two ways of praying.

01:20:47.480 --> 01:20:51.030 align:middle line:84%
One is where people pray for
something really specific,

01:20:51.030 --> 01:20:54.860 align:middle line:84%
make the cancer go away,
heal the heart attack,

01:20:54.860 --> 01:20:58.920 align:middle line:84%
versus people who used an
open-ended way of praying

01:20:58.920 --> 01:21:01.850 align:middle line:84%
in which they said, well,
may thy will be done,

01:21:01.850 --> 01:21:05.390 align:middle line:84%
or may the best thing happen,
without spelling it out.

01:21:05.390 --> 01:21:06.760 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

01:21:06.760 --> 01:21:08.480 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: There's
not much difference.

01:21:08.480 --> 01:21:08.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There's no
difference, really.

01:21:08.880 --> 01:21:11.110 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: There's
hardly any difference.

01:21:11.110 --> 01:21:13.640 align:middle line:84%
And so then the
question becomes, well,

01:21:13.640 --> 01:21:16.560 align:middle line:84%
what's going on here
if the strategy doesn't

01:21:16.560 --> 01:21:20.450 align:middle line:90%
happen to be of any consequence?

01:21:20.450 --> 01:21:24.149 align:middle line:90%
And it all boils down to love.

01:21:24.149 --> 01:21:25.940 align:middle line:84%
Because if you ask all
of those healers who

01:21:25.940 --> 01:21:28.340 align:middle line:84%
use these different
strategies, what's

01:21:28.340 --> 01:21:30.140 align:middle line:90%
the most important thing?

01:21:30.140 --> 01:21:32.410 align:middle line:90%
They'll say you've got to care.

01:21:32.410 --> 01:21:35.450 align:middle line:84%
You have got to feel it in
your heart, as we were saying,

01:21:35.450 --> 01:21:40.140 align:middle line:84%
and there has to be a real
heart connection here.

01:21:40.140 --> 01:21:41.994 align:middle line:90%
So love trumps religion.

01:21:41.994 --> 01:21:42.660 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It does.

01:21:42.660 --> 01:21:44.160 align:middle line:90%
It trumps science.

01:21:44.160 --> 01:21:47.384 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: It trumps everything
where this is concerned.

01:21:47.384 --> 01:21:49.050 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I've had the
amazing opportunity

01:21:49.050 --> 01:21:50.800 align:middle line:84%
to sit in this
chair and interview

01:21:50.800 --> 01:21:52.585 align:middle line:84%
visionaries such
as yourself, and do

01:21:52.585 --> 01:21:55.280 align:middle line:84%
you know how most of
those interviews end?

01:21:55.280 --> 01:21:57.144 align:middle line:90%
The same way.

01:21:57.144 --> 01:21:58.060 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: I love that.

01:21:58.060 --> 01:21:58.860 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: The same way.

01:21:58.860 --> 01:21:59.590 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I love it
when that happens.

01:21:59.590 --> 01:22:01.006 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Whether
or not I'm talking

01:22:01.006 --> 01:22:06.580 align:middle line:84%
about near-death experiences,
ancient civilizations, healing,

01:22:06.580 --> 01:22:10.420 align:middle line:84%
biology-- it all
comes down to love.

01:22:10.420 --> 01:22:12.650 align:middle line:90%
It is absolutely amazing.

01:22:12.650 --> 01:22:14.889 align:middle line:84%
We should put a reel
together of all the people

01:22:14.889 --> 01:22:16.180 align:middle line:90%
who said it comes down to love.

01:22:16.180 --> 01:22:18.429 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Yeah, well, that
would be fascinating to do.

01:22:18.429 --> 01:22:20.160 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It would
because it's true.

01:22:20.160 --> 01:22:23.370 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And if you try
to tease apart, break up,

01:22:23.370 --> 01:22:24.972 align:middle line:90%
what is this love business?

01:22:24.972 --> 01:22:25.930 align:middle line:90%
I mean, what's implied?

01:22:25.930 --> 01:22:26.513 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

01:22:26.513 --> 01:22:29.410 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And I think it's
the breakdown of boundaries

01:22:29.410 --> 01:22:30.900 align:middle line:90%
between people.

01:22:30.900 --> 01:22:35.110 align:middle line:84%
We build walls between each
other, as rugged individuals.

01:22:35.110 --> 01:22:40.110 align:middle line:84%
Our national ethos is built
on rugged individuality.

01:22:40.110 --> 01:22:42.380 align:middle line:84%
But love is the
opposite of that.

01:22:42.380 --> 01:22:45.050 align:middle line:84%
Love is a willingness
to break down

01:22:45.050 --> 01:22:49.567 align:middle line:84%
the barrier of separation
between people.

01:22:49.567 --> 01:22:51.150 align:middle line:84%
Actually, this gives
me an opportunity

01:22:51.150 --> 01:22:53.390 align:middle line:84%
to make a shameless
advertisement for a book

01:22:53.390 --> 01:22:55.122 align:middle line:90%
that I have finished.

01:22:55.122 --> 01:22:55.830 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, good.

01:22:55.830 --> 01:22:57.788 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: It will be
published in a few months.

01:22:57.788 --> 01:23:01.380 align:middle line:84%
It's called "The One Mind,"
how our individual minds are

01:23:01.380 --> 01:23:04.004 align:middle line:84%
part of a greater mind
and why it matters.

01:23:04.004 --> 01:23:05.670 align:middle line:84%
And the theme of the
book-- it goes back

01:23:05.670 --> 01:23:10.390 align:middle line:84%
through history viewing all of
the spiritual and philosophical

01:23:10.390 --> 01:23:13.240 align:middle line:84%
traditions which say
that, at some level,

01:23:13.240 --> 01:23:16.840 align:middle line:84%
there is an enveloping,
universal mind

01:23:16.840 --> 01:23:18.870 align:middle line:90%
of which our minds are a part.

01:23:18.870 --> 01:23:21.570 align:middle line:84%
And realizing that
requires the breakdown

01:23:21.570 --> 01:23:25.920 align:middle line:84%
of boundaries that
separate you from all

01:23:25.920 --> 01:23:28.300 align:middle line:84%
the other consciousnesses
and the one

01:23:28.300 --> 01:23:30.370 align:middle line:90%
mind of which we're a part.

01:23:30.370 --> 01:23:36.490 align:middle line:84%
And when people really do
this, healing power flourishes,

01:23:36.490 --> 01:23:37.390 align:middle line:90%
love blossoms--

01:23:37.390 --> 01:23:39.570 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Lives get easier.

01:23:39.570 --> 01:23:42.050 align:middle line:90%
Finances probably improve.

01:23:42.050 --> 01:23:43.940 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Often.

01:23:43.940 --> 01:23:48.090 align:middle line:84%
So I think that love is
a very fascinating idea.

01:23:48.090 --> 01:23:50.570 align:middle line:84%
But we have to get through
the romantic notion of it,

01:23:50.570 --> 01:23:51.840 align:middle line:90%
and the cultural versions.

01:23:51.840 --> 01:23:54.900 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It has the same
connotation that prayer has.

01:23:54.900 --> 01:23:56.990 align:middle line:84%
It's got a certain
image around love.

01:23:56.990 --> 01:23:58.610 align:middle line:84%
But I mean, if you
think about it,

01:23:58.610 --> 01:24:00.470 align:middle line:84%
has anyone at their
death bed ever said,

01:24:00.470 --> 01:24:03.210 align:middle line:84%
I really wish I would
have hated somebody more.

01:24:03.210 --> 01:24:03.890 align:middle line:90%
No.

01:24:03.890 --> 01:24:04.640 align:middle line:90%
It's the opposite.

01:24:04.640 --> 01:24:06.830 align:middle line:84%
It's, I wish I would have
healed that relationship

01:24:06.830 --> 01:24:08.040 align:middle line:90%
with my brother or mother.

01:24:08.040 --> 01:24:10.880 align:middle line:84%
I wish I would have let
go of that resentment.

01:24:10.880 --> 01:24:12.820 align:middle line:84%
I wish I'd forgiven
myself for this, that,

01:24:12.820 --> 01:24:16.470 align:middle line:84%
and the other that's all that
overarching theme of what

01:24:16.470 --> 01:24:18.750 align:middle line:90%
the universal love is.

01:24:18.750 --> 01:24:21.400 align:middle line:84%
And it's done from a
scientific perspective.

01:24:21.400 --> 01:24:23.070 align:middle line:84%
It's from a religious
perspective.

01:24:23.070 --> 01:24:25.730 align:middle line:84%
It's from a personal
development perspective.

01:24:25.730 --> 01:24:29.670 align:middle line:84%
Any way you look at it, it
all boils down to that theme.

01:24:29.670 --> 01:24:33.170 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I've had a fascinating
experience researching this

01:24:33.170 --> 01:24:36.220 align:middle line:84%
book on the one mind in terms
of looking at near-death

01:24:36.220 --> 01:24:40.440 align:middle line:84%
experiences where people after
death feel that they're united

01:24:40.440 --> 01:24:40.940 align:middle line:90%
with--

01:24:40.940 --> 01:24:41.480 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: All of consciousness.

01:24:41.480 --> 01:24:42.840 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: --all there is, right?

01:24:42.840 --> 01:24:43.250 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

01:24:43.250 --> 01:24:44.070 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's one thing.

01:24:44.070 --> 01:24:45.486 align:middle line:84%
The other thing
is they experience

01:24:45.486 --> 01:24:50.790 align:middle line:84%
an overwhelming, ineffable
sense of overpowering love.

01:24:50.790 --> 01:24:52.570 align:middle line:84%
And they almost all
come back saying,

01:24:52.570 --> 01:24:56.950 align:middle line:84%
I have never experienced
anything like this in my life.

